										<div class="inner_wrapper fullwidth">
								        
										<p><strong>Literary Hub and <a href="https://www.wildsam.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Wildsam</a> present: a literary road trip across America. </strong><strong>Happy travels!</strong></p><div class="insert-post-ads" style="clear:both;width:100%;margin:0 0 20px 0;"><span>Article continues after advertisement</span><script id="9b7a21a47fb44523b011db6d4f4cad23">(new Image()).src = 'https://capi.connatix.com/tr/si?token=546998bb-b9c0-4480-8c91-3e307220efff&cid=86b7c382-5e20-4129-84db-dea768f4d688';  cnx.cmd.push(function() {    cnx({      playerId: "546998bb-b9c0-4480-8c91-3e307220efff"    }).render("9b7a21a47fb44523b011db6d4f4cad23");  });</script></div><div class="insert-post-ads remove"><a href="https://lithub.memberful.com/join" target="_new" class="remove-ads external">Remove Ads</a></div>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Illustrations by Mike McKeogh</em></p>
<p><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241490" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/usa_map/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/USA_Map-scaled.jpg" data-orig-size="2560,2019" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="USA_Map" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/USA_Map-300x237.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/USA_Map-1240x978.jpg" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-241490" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/USA_Map-1240x978.jpg" alt="" width="1240" height="978" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/USA_Map-1240x978.jpg 1240w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/USA_Map-300x237.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/USA_Map-768x606.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/USA_Map-60x47.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/USA_Map-1536x1212.jpg 1536w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/USA_Map-2048x1615.jpg 2048w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/USA_Map-50x39.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1240px) 100vw, 1240px" /></p>
<h4 style="text-align: center;"><strong><a href="#northern-flicker"> Alabama</a> • <a href="#willow-ptarmigan">Alaska</a> • <a href="#cactus-wren">Arizona</a> • <a href="#cool-guru">Arkansas</a> • <a href="#california-quail">California</a> • <a href="#lark-bunting">Colorado</a> • <a href="#american-robin">Connecticut</a> • <a href="#blue-hen">Delaware</a> • <a href="#wood-thrush">District of Columbia</a> • <a href="#florida-mockingbird">Florida</a> • <a href="#brown-thrasher">Georgia</a> • <a href="#hawaiian-goose">Hawaii</a> • <a href="#mountain-bluebird">Idaho</a> • <a href="#northern-cardinal">Illinois</a> • <a href="#indiana-cardinal">Indiana</a> • <a href="#eastern-goldfinch">Iowa</a> • <a href="#western-meadowlark">Kansas</a> • <a href="#kentucky-cardinal">Kentucky</a> • <a href="#brown-pelican">Louisiana</a> • <a href="#chicka-dee">Maine</a> • <a href="#baltimore-oriole">Maryland</a> • <a href="#blackcapped-chickadee">Massachusetts</a> • <a href="#michigan-robin">Michigan</a> • <a href="#common-loon">Minnesota</a> • <a href="#mississippi-mockingbird">Mississippi</a> • <a href="#eastern-bluebird">Missouri</a> • <a href="#montana-meadowlark">Montana</a> • <a href="#nebraska-meadowlark">Nebraska</a> • <a href="#nevada-bluebird">Nevada</a> • <a href="#purple-finch">New Hampshire</a> • <a href="#american-goldfinch">New Jersey</a> • <a href="#greater-roadrunner">New Mexico</a> • <a href="#ny-bluebird">New York</a> • <a href="#nc-cardinal">North Carolina</a> • <a href="#nd-meadowlark">North Dakota</a> • <a href="#ohio-cardinal">Ohio</a> • <a href="#scissortailed-flycatcher">Oklahoma</a> • <a href="#oregon-meadowlark">Oregon</a> • <a href="#ruffed-grouse">Pennsylvania</a> • <a href="#rhodeisland-red">Rhode Island</a> • <a href="#carolina-wren">South Carolina</a> • <a href="#ringnecked-pheasant">South Dakota</a> • <a href="#tennessee-mockingbird">Tennessee</a> • <a href="#texas-mockingbird">Texas</a> • <a href="#california-gull">Utah</a> • <a href="#hermit-thrush">Vermont</a> • <a href="#virginia-cardinal">Virginia</a> • <a href="#willow-goldfinch">Washington</a> • <a href="#wv-cardinal">West Virginia</a> • <a href="#wisconsin-robin">Wisconsin</a> • <a href="#wyoming-meadowlark">Wyoming</a></strong></h4>
<p><span id="northern-flicker"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241388" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/alabama-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/alabama-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="alabama copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/alabama-copy-300x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/alabama-copy-1024x1024.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-241388" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/alabama-copy.jpg" alt="" width="704" height="704" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/alabama-copy.jpg 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/alabama-copy-300x300.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/alabama-copy-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/alabama-copy-150x150.jpg 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/alabama-copy-768x768.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/alabama-copy-60x60.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/alabama-copy-109x109.jpg 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/alabama-copy-100x100.jpg 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/alabama-copy-600x600.jpg 600w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/alabama-copy-50x50.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 704px) 100vw, 704px" /></span></p>
<h1>Alabama</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong><a href="https://littleprofessorbookshop.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Little Professor</a>, Homewood</h2>
<p>Visit the state&#8217;s oldest independent bookstore to find something new to fill up your brain—and then head a few blocks south to Johnny&#8217;s Restaurant, where you can fill up your belly (with fried green tomatoes). [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Little+Professor+Bookshop/@33.4796202,-86.7919923,15z/data=!4m5!3m4!1s0x0:0x9813caa9cc3442fb!8m2!3d33.4796202!4d-86.7919923?sa=X&amp;ved=2ahUKEwjD5eyN29v7AhWbNEQIHQX3BjQQ_BJ6BAh5EAg&amp;coh=164777&amp;entry=tt&amp;shorturl=1" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>]</p><div class="insert-post-ads" style="clear:both;width:100%;margin:0 0 20px 0;"><span>Article continues after advertisement</span><div class="htlad-LH_PP_IC"></div></div><div class="insert-post-ads remove"><a href="https://lithub.memberful.com/join" target="_new" class="remove-ads external">Remove Ads</a></div>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781984899767" class="external" target="_blank"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="129173" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2020/attachment/48270439/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/48270439.jpg" data-orig-size="302,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Yaa Gyasi, Transcendent Kingdom" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/48270439-201x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/48270439.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-129173 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/48270439-201x300.jpg" alt="Yaa Gyasi, Transcendent Kingdom" width="201" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/48270439-201x300.jpg 201w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/48270439-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/48270439.jpg 302w" sizes="(max-width: 201px) 100vw, 201px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781984899767" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Transcendent Kingdom</em></a><br />
by Yaa Gyasi</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">Gifty and her family leave Ghana for Huntsville in this novel drawn from Gyasi&#8217;s life as the daughter of immigrants. [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Huntsville,+AL/@34.7013171,-86.8249027,11z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x88626b67cda2898d:0x9a2c7e89c804566b!8m2!3d34.7303688!4d-86.5861037!16zL20vMHE4c3c?entry=ttu" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>]</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780306818363" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240418" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/612vnt5wdol-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/612vnT5wdOL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Salvation on Sand Mountain" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/612vnT5wdOL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/612vnT5wdOL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-240418 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/612vnT5wdOL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-200x300.jpg" alt="Salvation on Sand Mountain" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/612vnT5wdOL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/612vnT5wdOL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/612vnT5wdOL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/612vnT5wdOL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 667w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></a></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780306818363" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Salvation on Sand Mountain</em></a><br />
by Dennis Covington</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">A National Book Award finalist, Covington&#8217;s book covers the trial of Glenn Summerford and a snake handling church in Appalachia with generous curiosity. [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Scottsboro,+AL/@34.6419687,-86.1285918,12z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x8861eee05dbd8549:0x90c2e9f1ec964bff!8m2!3d34.6723069!4d-86.0341463!16zL20vMHE3djQ?entry=ttu" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241517" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-copy-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241517" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://ashleymjonespoetry.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Ashley M. Jones</a></h2>
<p>Jones is Alabama&#8217;s current poet laureate; her 2021 collection <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781938235863" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>REPARATIONS NOW!</em></a> was longlisted for the PEN / Voelker Award.</p><div class="insert-post-ads" style="clear:both;width:100%;margin:0 0 20px 0;"><span>Article continues after advertisement</span><div class="htlad-LH_PP_IC"></div></div><div class="insert-post-ads remove"><a href="https://lithub.memberful.com/join" target="_new" class="remove-ads external">Remove Ads</a></div>
