<h1>Alaska</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong><a href="https://library.alaska.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Alaska State Library</a>, Juneau</h2>
<p>The archives, stacks, and reading rooms here don’t skimp on majesty, and the design of the library itself—perched waterside and flanked by Thunder, Jumbo, Juneau, Roberts, and McGinnis peaks—is evocative of a bird poised for flight. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/Yv3KweNtXN7EYVTCA" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<h4><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780064400589" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240424" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/julie-of-the-wolves/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/julie-of-the-wolves.jpeg" data-orig-size="269,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="julie of the wolves" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/julie-of-the-wolves-202x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/julie-of-the-wolves.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240424 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/julie-of-the-wolves-202x300.jpeg" alt="" width="202" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/julie-of-the-wolves-202x300.jpeg 202w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/julie-of-the-wolves-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/julie-of-the-wolves-34x50.jpeg 34w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/julie-of-the-wolves.jpeg 269w" sizes="(max-width: 202px) 100vw, 202px" /></a></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780064400589" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Julie of the Wolves</em></a><br />
by Jean Craighead George</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">This tale of an Inuit girl and her adoptive wolf pack is an adventure classic. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/PjCx4qW8821gybeQ7?coh=178573&amp;entry=tt" target="_blank">MAP</a>] <em>See also:</em> <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780007149834" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The</em> <em>Yiddish Policeman&#8217;s Union</em></a> by Michael Chabon</p><div class="insert-post-ads" style="clear:both;width:100%;margin:0 0 20px 0;"><span>Article continues after advertisement</span><div class="htlad-LH_PP_IC"></div></div><div class="insert-post-ads remove"><a href="https://lithub.memberful.com/join" target="_new" class="remove-ads external">Remove Ads</a></div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374522872" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240425" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/coming-into-the-country/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Coming-into-the-Country.jpeg" data-orig-size="270,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Coming into the Country" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Coming-into-the-Country-203x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Coming-into-the-Country.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240425 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Coming-into-the-Country-203x300.jpeg" alt="" width="203" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Coming-into-the-Country-203x300.jpeg 203w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Coming-into-the-Country-41x60.jpeg 41w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Coming-into-the-Country-34x50.jpeg 34w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Coming-into-the-Country.jpeg 270w" sizes="(max-width: 203px) 100vw, 203px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374522872" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Coming into the Country</em></a><br />
by John McPhee</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">A master observer of place and people, McPhee&#8217;s travels through Alaska introduce readers to prospectors, politicians, and the bush community of Eagle. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/2qS8MCvxTh7aCFJA9" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
