<h1>Arizona</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong><a href="https://www.desertmuseum.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Arizona-Sonora Desert Museum</a>, Tucson</h2>
<p>Find 98 acres of botanical garden for walks and many desert landscape reading spots among sky-high saguaros. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/eLN94W4fxv16YRBH7" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780062278500" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240432" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/77262-1/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/77262-1-scaled.jpg" data-orig-size="1694,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="animal dreams barbara kingsolver" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/77262-1-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/77262-1-678x1024.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-240432 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/77262-1-199x300.jpg" alt="animal dreams barbara kingsolver" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/77262-1-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/77262-1-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/77262-1-768x1161.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/77262-1-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/77262-1-1016x1536.jpg 1016w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/77262-1-1355x2048.jpg 1355w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/77262-1-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/77262-1-scaled.jpg 1694w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780062278500" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Animal Dreams</em></a><br />
by Barbara Kingsolver</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">Cosima &#8220;Codi&#8221; Noline returns to her rural Arizona home in Kingsolver&#8217;s 1990 novel, a meditation on grief, family, and homecoming. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/sXqgQsVGz4QvJhBw8" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250251237" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240433" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/the-death-and-life-of-aida-hernandez-a-border-story/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Death-and-Life-of-Aida-Hernandez-A-Border-Story.jpeg" data-orig-size="261,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The Death and Life of Aida Hernandez- A Border Story" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Death-and-Life-of-Aida-Hernandez-A-Border-Story-196x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Death-and-Life-of-Aida-Hernandez-A-Border-Story.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240433 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Death-and-Life-of-Aida-Hernandez-A-Border-Story-196x300.jpeg" alt="The Death and Life of Aida Hernandez- A Border Story" width="196" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Death-and-Life-of-Aida-Hernandez-A-Border-Story-196x300.jpeg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Death-and-Life-of-Aida-Hernandez-A-Border-Story-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Death-and-Life-of-Aida-Hernandez-A-Border-Story-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Death-and-Life-of-Aida-Hernandez-A-Border-Story.jpeg 261w" sizes="(max-width: 196px) 100vw, 196px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250251237" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Death and Life of Aida Hernandez: A Border Story</em></a><br />
by Aaron Bobrow-Strain</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">What happens when an undocumented teen mother takes on the U.S. immigration system? This book is a harrowing deep-dive into the cost of the American dream. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/LXW3oqesM9QnikJt6" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241519" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-arizona/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill arizona" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241519" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.poetryfoundation.org/poets/natalie-diaz" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Natalie Diaz</a></h2>
<p>A recipient of the MacArthur &#8220;Genius&#8221; Grant whose latest collection, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781644450147" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Postcolonial Love Poem</em></a>, won the 2021 Pulitzer Prize for poetry, Diaz teaches at Arizona State University, and has directed a Mojave language revitalization project at Fort Mohave. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/2GFq1tJcC4NkLX7GA" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241162" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/poetrycenter/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/poetrycenter.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="poetrycenter" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/poetrycenter.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/poetrycenter.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241162" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/poetrycenter.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/poetrycenter.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/poetrycenter-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/poetrycenter-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/poetrycenter-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/poetrycenter-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/poetrycenter-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong><a href="https://poetry.arizona.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Poetry Center</a></h2>
<p>Poet Steve Orlen called the Helen S. Schaefer Building—home base of The Poetry Center at University of Arizona—&#8221;the best living room in America for reading poetry.&#8221; [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/a9hHm8dXkvfD4aJD8" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
