<h1>Arkansas</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong><a href="https://crystalbridges.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Crystal Bridges Museum of American Art</a>, Bentonville</h2>
<p>Moshe Safdie designed this stunning structure in harmony with surrounding mountain landscape; you can find a rare Frank Lloyd Wright Usonian house here, too. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/Q9JBxwUXb8GUTfCf7" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781590204597" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240436" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/truegrit/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/truegrit.jpeg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="true grit" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/truegrit-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/truegrit.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240436 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/truegrit-200x300.jpeg" alt="true grit" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/truegrit-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/truegrit-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/truegrit-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/truegrit.jpeg 667w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781590204597" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>True Grit</em></a><br />
by Charles Portis</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">Mattie Ross is 14 when she sets out across western Arkansas seeking justice for the murder of her father; adventure ensues! [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/QwN6tJCyqzmyhMdE9" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781682260906" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240437" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/hipbillies-deep-revolution-in-the-arkansas-ozarks/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Hipbillies-Deep-Revolution-in-the-Arkansas-Ozarks.jpeg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Hipbillies- Deep Revolution in the Arkansas Ozarks" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Hipbillies-Deep-Revolution-in-the-Arkansas-Ozarks-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Hipbillies-Deep-Revolution-in-the-Arkansas-Ozarks.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240437 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Hipbillies-Deep-Revolution-in-the-Arkansas-Ozarks-200x300.jpeg" alt="Hipbillies- Deep Revolution in the Arkansas Ozarks" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Hipbillies-Deep-Revolution-in-the-Arkansas-Ozarks-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Hipbillies-Deep-Revolution-in-the-Arkansas-Ozarks-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Hipbillies-Deep-Revolution-in-the-Arkansas-Ozarks-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Hipbillies-Deep-Revolution-in-the-Arkansas-Ozarks.jpeg 667w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781682260906" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Hipbillies: Deep Revolution in the Arkansas Ozarks</em></a><br />
by Jared M. Phillips</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">This archival deep-dive of Ozark beatniks is a departure from more common tales of the counterculture. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/TJTSUWnci2qtfq6k9" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
