<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://encyclopediaofarkansas.net/entries/rosa-zagnoni-marinoni-1705/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Rosa Zagnoni Marinoni</a></h2>
<p>In 1926, Marinoni created the University-City Poetry Club; for forty-five years, the club met at her home near the UA campus. In 1953, she was named poet laureate of Arkansas. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/sHSTs5Cby2KWT8oy8" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241163" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/johnswood/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/johnswood.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="johnswood" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/johnswood.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/johnswood.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241163" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/johnswood.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/johnswood.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/johnswood-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/johnswood-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/johnswood-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/johnswood-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/johnswood-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong><a href="https://encyclopediaofarkansas.net/entries/johnswood-15790/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Johnswood</a></h2>
<p>John Gould Fletcher and Charlie May Simon lived here, writing from opposite sides of the house. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/sKYCFRUBp4wFPRKXA" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/arkansas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more on Literary Arkansas</a></strong></h2>
<p><span id="california-quail"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241382" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/california-copy2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/california-copy2.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="california copy2" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/california-copy2-300x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/california-copy2-1024x1024.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-241382 " src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/california-copy2.jpg" alt="" width="777" height="777" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/california-copy2.jpg 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/california-copy2-300x300.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/california-copy2-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/california-copy2-150x150.jpg 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/california-copy2-768x768.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/california-copy2-60x60.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/california-copy2-109x109.jpg 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/california-copy2-100x100.jpg 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/california-copy2-600x600.jpg 600w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/california-copy2-50x50.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 777px) 100vw, 777px" /></span></p>
<h1>California</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong><a href="https://www.nepenthe.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Nepenthe</a>, Big Sur</h2>
<p>Named for the sorrow-dispelling drug in Homer&#8217;s <em>Odyssey</em>, this perch is known for its dramatic Pacific views (and vibes); literary legends haunt these parts. If you need a change of scenery, the <a href="https://www.henrymiller.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Henry Miller Memorial Library</a> is right down the road. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/Gsw3YerptyD5KnYY8" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374604516" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="192809" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/18-new-books-hitting-shelves-this-week/mecca_susan-straight/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/mecca_susan-straight.jpeg" data-orig-size="1650,2531" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="mecca_susan straight" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/mecca_susan-straight-196x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/mecca_susan-straight-668x1024.jpeg" class="alignleft wp-image-192809 size-medium" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/mecca_susan-straight-196x300.jpeg" alt="mecca_susan straight" width="196" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/mecca_susan-straight-196x300.jpeg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/mecca_susan-straight-668x1024.jpeg 668w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/mecca_susan-straight-768x1178.jpeg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/mecca_susan-straight-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/mecca_susan-straight-1001x1536.jpeg 1001w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/mecca_susan-straight-1335x2048.jpeg 1335w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/mecca_susan-straight-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/mecca_susan-straight.jpeg 1650w" sizes="(max-width: 196px) 100vw, 196px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374604516" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><i>Mecca</i></a><br />
by Susan Straight</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">There is no glitz and no glamour in Straight&#8217;s recent novel, which makes it all the more essential as a California epic. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Riverside,+CA/@33.9459881,-117.4819282,12z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x80dca6df7ff47dbb:0xf7a1d705135e0ae8!8m2!3d33.9806005!4d-117.3754942!16zL20vMHIzd20?entry=ttu" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MAP</a>] <em>See also:</em> <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780802124944" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Sympathizer</em></a> by Viet Thanh Nguyen; <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780394758275" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Farewell, My Lovely</em></a> by Raymond Chandler</p>
<h4></h4>
<h4></h4>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374531386" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241381" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/slouching-towards-bethelem/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Slouching-Towards-Bethelem.jpg" data-orig-size="300,449" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Slouching-Towards-Bethelem" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Slouching-Towards-Bethelem-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Slouching-Towards-Bethelem.jpg" class="alignright wp-image-241381 size-medium" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Slouching-Towards-Bethelem-200x300.jpg" alt="Slouching-Towards-Bethelem" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Slouching-Towards-Bethelem-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Slouching-Towards-Bethelem-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Slouching-Towards-Bethelem-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Slouching-Towards-Bethelem.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374531386" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Slouching Towards Bethlehem</em></a><br />
by Joan Didion</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">Possibly the most iconic California book (and California writer) of all time. [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Haight-Ashbury,+San+Francisco,+CA+94117/@37.7696509,-122.4512569,16z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x808580ac9f32f45f:0x324dc0abe78d0a48!8m2!3d37.7702175!4d-122.4453615!16zL20vMDIzeDg4?entry=ttu" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>] <em>See also:</em> <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781590178904" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Eve’s Hollywood</em></a> by Eve Babitz</p>
