<h1>Connecticut</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong><a href="https://beinecke.library.yale.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Beinecke Rare Book &amp; Manuscript Library</a>, New Haven</h2>
<p>A cathedral of 180,000 volumes (and thousands of linear feet) plus jaw-dropping permanent collections, all accessible for free—heaven for bibliophiles. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/HbzzbXf6pFmeUDGu5" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780375708442" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="89588" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/30-of-the-worst-couples-in-literature/revolutionary-road-4/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/revolutionary-road.jpg" data-orig-size="314,485" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="revolutionary-road" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/revolutionary-road-194x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/revolutionary-road.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-89588 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/revolutionary-road-194x300.jpg" alt="revolutionary road book cover" width="194" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/revolutionary-road-194x300.jpg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/revolutionary-road.jpg 314w" sizes="(max-width: 194px) 100vw, 194px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780375708442" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Revolutionary Road</em></a><br />
by Richard Yates</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">Trouble brews in a suburban idyll when conventions are questioned and tested. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/nWrsUaQkPyPfSSkc9" target="_blank">MAP</a>] <em>See also:</em> <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780525562047" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>On Earth We&#8217;re Briefly Gorgeous</em></a> by Ocean Vuong; <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250751362" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Ninth House</em></a> by Leigh Bardugo</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781728234618" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240501" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/yale-needs-women/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/yale-needs-women.jpeg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="yale needs women" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/yale-needs-women-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/yale-needs-women.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240501 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/yale-needs-women-200x300.jpeg" alt="" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/yale-needs-women-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/yale-needs-women-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/yale-needs-women-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/yale-needs-women.jpeg 667w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781728234618" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Yale Needs Women</em></a><br />
by Anne Gardiner Perkins</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">In 1969, five women broke the gender barrier at Yale for the first time; this Connecticut Book Award-winning account follows them through the school’s early years of coeducation. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/k6upBdPkwZTahXz27" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
