<h1>Florida</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong>Florida Keys National Marine Sanctuary, Miami to Dry Tortugas</h2>
<p>Nearly 3,000 square nautical miles of coastal and ocean ecosystem teeming with fish, coral, and birds. Protected, but free. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/CKAjDEY3ftLucMJ1A" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<h4><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781594634529" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="96445" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/is-this-the-biggest-book-cover-trend-of-the-year/floridabylaurengroff/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/floridabylaurengroff.jpg" data-orig-size="300,469" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="floridabylaurengroff" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/floridabylaurengroff-192x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/floridabylaurengroff.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-96445 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/floridabylaurengroff-192x300.jpg" alt="florida" width="192" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/floridabylaurengroff-192x300.jpg 192w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/floridabylaurengroff.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 192px) 100vw, 192px" /></a></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781594634529" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Florida</em></a><br />
by Lauren Groff</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">Nature means menace in this lush collection of short stories from three-time National Book Award finalist Groff, who lives and teaches in Gainesville. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/8iPMmTJUVvmqQyaH9" target="_blank">MAP</a>] <em>See also</em>: <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780345804341" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Nickel Boys</em></a> by Colson Whitehead.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780449003718" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="159658" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/trouble-for-your-thoughts-on-reported-creative-nonfiction/71nfalo4jnl/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/71nfAlo4JnL.jpg" data-orig-size="1647,2481" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Susan Orlean, The Orchid Thief" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/71nfAlo4JnL-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/71nfAlo4JnL-680x1024.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-159658 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/71nfAlo4JnL-199x300.jpg" alt="Susan Orlean, The Orchid Thief" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/71nfAlo4JnL-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/71nfAlo4JnL-680x1024.jpg 680w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/71nfAlo4JnL-768x1157.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/71nfAlo4JnL-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/71nfAlo4JnL-1020x1536.jpg 1020w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/71nfAlo4JnL-1360x2048.jpg 1360w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/71nfAlo4JnL.jpg 1647w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780449003718" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Orchid Thief</em></a><br />
by Susan Orlean</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">Orlean&#8217;s investigation of the 1994 arrest of horticulturist John Laroche and a group of Seminoles in south Florida for poaching rare orchids also served as the (very meta) <a href="https://lithub.com/13-adaptations-better-than-the-books-theyre-based-on/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">inspiration for the film <em>Adaptation</em></a>. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/97Rx6LwLWjYzKHoe9" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241520" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-arkansas/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill arkansas" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241520" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.poetryfoundation.org/poets/elizabeth-bishop" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Elizabeth Bishop</a></h2>
<p><em>Poems, Prose and Letters</em> includes poetry from the Pulitzer Prize and National Book Award winner&#8217;s time in the Keys. Start with “Roosters.” [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/aaNXWLbvE4Nvsiwj6" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241199" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/znh/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/znh.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="znh" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/znh.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/znh.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241199" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/znh.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/znh.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/znh-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/znh-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/znh-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/znh-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/znh-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong>Zora Neale Hurston House, Fort Pierce</h2>
<p>Hurston&#8217;s childhood was spent in Eatonville, one of the first all-Black towns incorporated in the United States. But the last remaining residence associated with the beloved author is this one, in nearby Fort Pierce, where she lived toward the end of her life. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Zora+Neale+Hurston+House/@27.4613576,-80.3456445,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x88def1617e576039:0x1f73b2c2d1948fdf!8m2!3d27.4613576!4d-80.3430642!16zL20vMGgzOWts?entry=ttu" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/florida/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Read more on Literary Florida</strong></a></h2>
<h2>(Or Spend a Literary Long Weekend in <a href="https://lithub.com/literary-long-weekend-tampa-bay-area/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tampa</a>, or Read <a href="https://lithub.com/5-reasons-why-a-writer-should-move-to-tampa/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">5 Reasons Why Writers Should Move to Tampa</a>)</h2>
<p><span id="brown-thrasher"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241442" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/georgia-copy2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/georgia-copy2.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="georgia copy2" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/georgia-copy2-300x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/georgia-copy2-1024x1024.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-241442" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/georgia-copy2.jpg" alt="" width="746" height="746" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/georgia-copy2.jpg 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/georgia-copy2-300x300.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/georgia-copy2-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/georgia-copy2-150x150.jpg 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/georgia-copy2-768x768.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/georgia-copy2-60x60.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/georgia-copy2-109x109.jpg 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/georgia-copy2-100x100.jpg 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/georgia-copy2-600x600.jpg 600w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/georgia-copy2-50x50.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 746px) 100vw, 746px" /