<h1>Georgia</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong><a href="https://www.spelman.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Spelman College</a>, Atlanta</h2>
<p>Reading spots abound on the 39 verdant acres of this historically Black college, where luminaries like Alice Walker and Martin Luther King Jr. once crossed paths. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/x5nASGyLRie1HwCa8" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9789357990325" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="15597" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-your-new-roommates-favorite-book-says-about-them/heartisalonelyhunter-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/HeartIsALonelyHunter.jpg" data-orig-size="220,317" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The Heart Is a Lonely Hunter" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/HeartIsALonelyHunter-208x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/HeartIsALonelyHunter.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-15597 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/HeartIsALonelyHunter-208x300.jpg" alt="The Heart Is a Lonely Hunter" width="208" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/HeartIsALonelyHunter-208x300.jpg 208w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/HeartIsALonelyHunter.jpg 220w" sizes="(max-width: 208px) 100vw, 208px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9789357990325" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Heart is a Lonely Hunter</em></a><br />
by Carson McCullers</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">A rich, humane exploration of spiritual isolation in a rural Georgia mill town. <em>See also</em>: <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781616208684" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>An American Marriage</em></a> by Tayari Jones.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780062914675" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="159058" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2021/81zvgen0gl/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/81zvgeN0GL.jpg" data-orig-size="1600,2407" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Charles M. Blow, The Devil You Know" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/81zvgeN0GL-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/81zvgeN0GL-681x1024.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-159058 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/81zvgeN0GL-199x300.jpg" alt="Charles M. Blow, The Devil You Know" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/81zvgeN0GL-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/81zvgeN0GL-681x1024.jpg 681w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/81zvgeN0GL-768x1155.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/81zvgeN0GL-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/81zvgeN0GL-1021x1536.jpg 1021w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/81zvgeN0GL-1361x2048.jpg 1361w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/81zvgeN0GL.jpg 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780062914675" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Devil You Know</em></a><br />
by Charles Blow</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">This journalist’s manifesto is also a call to action, asking Black Americans to migrate back south. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/ZX2Ypw6pND63cZ7W8" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241517" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-copy-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241517" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://chelsearathburn.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Chelsea Rathburn</a></h2>
<p>The author of <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780807169742" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Still Life with Mother</em> <em>and</em> <em>Knife</em></a> also implemented the Georgia Poetry in the Parks project. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/oVQgYvYPtGmxqYoaA" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241249" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/foc/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/foc.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="foc" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/foc.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/foc.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241249" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/foc.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/foc.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/foc-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/foc-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/foc-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/foc-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/foc-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong><a href="https://www.flanneryoconnorhome.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Flannery O&#8217;Connor Home</a>, Savannah</h2>
<p>The iconic spinner of Southern Gothic stories grew up in this house, where she famously kept a chicken who walked backwards. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/hzs3YwshH6JWuHg29" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
