<h1>Idaho</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong><a href="https://visitsunvalley.com/to-do/ernest-hemingway/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Hemingway Memorial</a>, Sun Valley</h2>
<p>Take a walk along Trail Creek and stop to rest and read for a while by the Hemingway Memorial, a simple column among the trees. For the slightly more morbid, his gravesite is also nearby, in Ketchum Cemetery. [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Hemingway+Memorial/@43.7122431,-114.3426199,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x54a99cc3151b86f7:0xd52a41bcbb736d48!8m2!3d43.7122431!4d-114.340045!16s%2Fg%2F11bzrv7v_p?entry=ttu" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250769763" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="139721" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/our-personalized-quarantine-book-recommendations-round-9/81x47nxkdwl/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/81X47NXkDWL.jpg" data-orig-size="1650,2475" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="housekeeping robinson" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/81X47NXkDWL-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/81X47NXkDWL-683x1024.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-139721 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/81X47NXkDWL-200x300.jpg" alt="housekeeping robinson" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/81X47NXkDWL-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/81X47NXkDWL-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/81X47NXkDWL-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/81X47NXkDWL-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/81X47NXkDWL-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/81X47NXkDWL-1365x2048.jpg 1365w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/81X47NXkDWL.jpg 1650w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250769763" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Housekeeping</em></a><br />
by Marilynne Robinson</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">Fingerbone, Idaho is a living, breathing character in this novel, from Pulitzer Prize winner Robinson, about three generations of women and the homes they make—both material and interior. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/GM5ojyjG79eCv9idA" target="_blank">MAP</a>] See also: <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250007650" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Train Dreams</em></a> by Denis Johnson</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780399590528" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="104211" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/announcing-the-2018-reading-women-award-winners/west_9780399590504_jkt_all_r2-indd/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Educated-Tara-Westover.jpg" data-orig-size="750,1140" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;west_9780399590504_jkt_all_r2.indd&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="west_9780399590504_jkt_all_r2.indd" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Educated-Tara-Westover-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Educated-Tara-Westover-674x1024.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-104211 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Educated-Tara-Westover-197x300.jpg" alt="" width="197" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Educated-Tara-Westover-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Educated-Tara-Westover-674x1024.jpg 674w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Educated-Tara-Westover.jpg 750w" sizes="(max-width: 197px) 100vw, 197px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780399590528" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Educated</em></a><br />
by Tara Westover</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">In this memoir, Westover, born to survivalist Mormon parents in Clifton, shares her harrowing experience of education in the rural Idaho of her childhood, and her journey beyond the confines of her family. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/fYV7EZXkg2UKSmPg6" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241523" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-ct/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill ct" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241523" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.cmariefuhrman.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">CMarie Fuhrman</a></h2>
<p>The state’s current Writer in Residence creates poetry inspired by landscape and wilderness and rooted in her Indigenous experience. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/Q6hzM6Qdsafisa9eA" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
