<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong><a href="https://www.idahoheritagetrust.org/projects-grants/ezra-pound-house/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Homer Pound House</a>, Hailey</h2>
<p>Sun Valley Center for the Arts is the steward of famed modernist poet Ezra Pound’s birthplace. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/yjNhNjxSX464hzBw9" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/idaho/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more on Literary Idaho</a></strong></h2>
<p><span id="northern-cardinal"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241337" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/il-concept-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/IL-concept-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="IL concept copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/IL-concept-copy-300x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/IL-concept-copy-1024x1024.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-241337" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/IL-concept-copy-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="787" height="787" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/IL-concept-copy-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/IL-concept-copy-300x300.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/IL-concept-copy-150x150.jpg 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/IL-concept-copy-768x768.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/IL-concept-copy-60x60.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/IL-concept-copy-109x109.jpg 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/IL-concept-copy-100x100.jpg 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/IL-concept-copy-600x600.jpg 600w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/IL-concept-copy-50x50.jpg 50w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/IL-concept-copy.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 787px) 100vw, 787px" /></span></p>
<h1>Illinois</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong>Ray Bradbury Park, Waukegan</h2>
<p>This lovely little park, dedicated to the Waukegan native and science fiction legend, is a good spot to spend an uninterrupted hour traveling the universe via book. [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Ray+Bradbury+Park/@42.36095,-87.8404549,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x880fed43ab6677e9:0x95e6ba07f6ee9c0c!8m2!3d42.36095!4d-87.83788!16s%2Fg%2F1tgx762w?entry=ttu" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780735223530" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="133561" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/heres-the-shortlist-for-the-50000-joyce-carol-oates-prize/the-great-believers_rebecca-makkai/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/The-Great-Believers_Rebecca-Makkai.jpg" data-orig-size="1690,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The Great Believers_Rebecca Makkai" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/The-Great-Believers_Rebecca-Makkai-198x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/The-Great-Believers_Rebecca-Makkai-676x1024.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-133561 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/The-Great-Believers_Rebecca-Makkai-198x300.jpg" alt="The Great Believers_Rebecca Makkai" width="198" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/The-Great-Believers_Rebecca-Makkai-198x300.jpg 198w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/The-Great-Believers_Rebecca-Makkai-676x1024.jpg 676w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/The-Great-Believers_Rebecca-Makkai-768x1163.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/The-Great-Believers_Rebecca-Makkai-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/The-Great-Believers_Rebecca-Makkai-1014x1536.jpg 1014w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/The-Great-Believers_Rebecca-Makkai-1352x2048.jpg 1352w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/The-Great-Believers_Rebecca-Makkai.jpg 1690w" sizes="(max-width: 198px) 100vw, 198px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780735223530" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Great Believers</em></a><br />
by Rebecca Makkai</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">The AIDS crisis infiltrates and upends a community of friends in 1980s Chicago in this multi-generational novel. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/PKjc3Ja8sT36da657" target="_blank">MAP</a>] <em>See also</em>: <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780143039570" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Adventures of Augie March</em></a> by Saul Bellow</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780679763888" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="124941" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-20-best-works-of-nonfiction-of-the-decade/a1pa5ofqwel/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/A1pa5OFqWEL.jpg" data-orig-size="1694,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="the warmth of other suns" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/A1pa5OFqWEL-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/A1pa5OFqWEL-678x1024.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-124941 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/A1pa5OFqWEL-199x300.jpg" alt="the warmth of other suns" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/A1pa5OFqWEL-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/A1pa5OFqWEL-768x1161.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/A1pa5OFqWEL-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/A1pa5OFqWEL-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/A1pa5OFqWEL.jpg 1694w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780679763888" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Warmth of Other Suns</em></a><br />
by Isabel Wilkerson</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">Wilkerson interviewed more than a thousand people in the crafting of this masterwork about the migration of Black Americans to northern and western cities. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/38edQnJemRGuzett6" target="_blank">MAP</a>] <em>See also</em>: <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780375725609" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Devil in the White City</em></a> by Erik Larson</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241534" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-ill/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ill.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill ill" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ill-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ill.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241534" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ill.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ill.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ill-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ill-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ill-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ill-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.poetryfoundation.org/poets/patricia-smith" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Patricia Smith</a></h2>
<p>The decorated Chicago-born poet is the author of eight collections and is the four-time individual champion of the National Poetry Slam. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/PPuREeza5TBBYBY19" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241205" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/wright-5/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wright.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="wright" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wright.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wright.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241205" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wright.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wright.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wright-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wright-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wright-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wright-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wright-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong><a href="https://webapps1.chicago.gov/landmarksweb/web/landmarkdetails.htm?lanId=13006" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Richard Wright House</a>, Chicago</h2>
<p>Wright&#8217;s seminal 1940 novel <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780060837563" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Native Son</em></a> was written in this four-room Bronzeville apartment. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/17CfbFBnrK1MTsgv7" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/Illinois/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more on Literary Illinois</a></strong></h2>
<h2>(Or Spend a Literary Long Weekend in <a href="https://lithub.com/how-to-spend-a-literary-long-weekend-in-chicago/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Chicago</a>)</h2>
<p><span id="indiana-cardinal"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241353" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/indiana-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/indiana-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="indiana copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/indiana-copy-300x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/indiana-copy-1024x1024.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-241353" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/indiana-copy-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="759" height="759" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/indiana-copy-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/indiana-copy-300x300.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/indiana-copy-150x150.jpg 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/indiana-copy-768x768.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/indiana-copy-60x60.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/indiana-copy-109x109.jpg 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/indiana-copy-100x100.jpg 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/indiana-copy-600x600.jpg 600w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/indiana-copy-50x50.jpg 50w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/indiana-copy.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 759px) 100vw, 759px" /></span></p>
<h1>Indiana</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong><a href="https://www.nps.gov/indu/index.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Indiana Dunes National Park</a>, Porter</h2>
<p>Inspiration should be easy to find in this lush expanse of shifting sand dunes, wetlands, oak savannahs and 15,000 acres of plant and bird variety. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/mMTzwTj5UwSNr4QN8" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593313329" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240511" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/an-american-tragedy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/an-american-tragedy.jpeg" data-orig-size="259,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="an american tragedy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/an-american-tragedy-194x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/an-american-tragedy.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240511 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/an-american-tragedy-194x300.jpeg" alt="" width="194" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/an-american-tragedy-194x300.jpeg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/an-american-tragedy-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/an-american-tragedy-32x50.jpeg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/an-american-tragedy.jpeg 259w" sizes="(max-width: 194px) 100vw, 194px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593313329" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>An American Tragedy</em></a><br />
by Theodore Dreiser</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">A Terre Haute native, Dreiser published this novel—a study of a notorious murder case, and a resounding indictment of American society—in 1925. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/SzqZpubT2jrTB5rE6" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781643753287" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="162521" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/flight-patterns-reading-of-the-creatures-of-the-air/71lwqnc4ucl/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/71lWQNC4uCL.jpg" data-orig-size="1575,2177" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Ross Gay, The Book of Delights" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/71lWQNC4uCL-217x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/71lWQNC4uCL-741x1024.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-162521 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/71lWQNC4uCL-217x300.jpg" alt="Ross Gay, The Book of Delights" width="217" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/71lWQNC4uCL-217x300.jpg 217w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/71lWQNC4uCL-741x1024.jpg 741w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/71lWQNC4uCL-768x1062.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/71lWQNC4uCL-43x60.jpg 43w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/71lWQNC4uCL-1111x1536.jpg 1111w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/71lWQNC4uCL-1482x2048.jpg 1482w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/71lWQNC4uCL-36x50.jpg 36w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/71lWQNC4uCL.jpg 1575w" sizes="(max-width: 217px) 100vw, 217px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781643753287" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Book of Delights</em></a><br />
by Ross Gay</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">An exploration of daily joys and wonder from an Indiana University professor and beloved lyricist. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/iuuLGqBFZbhU8r4x8" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241522" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-colorado/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill colorado" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241522" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.joyellemcsweeney.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Joyelle McSweeney</a></h2>
<p>McSweeney&#8217;s <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781643620183" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Toxicon and Arachne</em></a>, a volume of two books on disaster and the catastrophic, is brilliant and unsettling. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/M8g2HnvBZ9SZpW2u8" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241206" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/hutch/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/hutch.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="hutch" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/hutch.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/hutch.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241206" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/hutch.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/hutch.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/hutch-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/hutch-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/hutch-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/hutch-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/hutch-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></h2>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong>South Bend</h2>
<p>The fictional town of Vacca Vale, IN, where Tess Gunty&#8217;s National Book Award-winning <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593467879" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Rabbit Hutch</em></a> is set, is based on South Bend, where Gunty grew up. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/TB8zUJhniyRSjfj78" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/Indiana/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more on Literary Indiana</a></h2>
<p><span id="eastern-goldfinch"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241351" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/iowa-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/iowa-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,761" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="iowa copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/iowa-copy-300x190.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/iowa-copy.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-241351" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/iowa-copy.jpg" alt="" width="711" height="451" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/iowa-copy.jpg 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/iowa-copy-300x190.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/iowa-copy-768x487.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/iowa-copy-60x38.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/iowa-copy-660x420.jpg 660w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/iowa-copy-50x32.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 711px) 100vw, 711px" /></span></p>
<h1>Iowa</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong>Art Building West, Iowa City</h2>
<p>The shining edifice of this University of Iowa building is a sight to behold—and is surrounded by plenty of good reading spots. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/HLpwWMzCwHYz8vMh9" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781400033836" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240519" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/a-thousand-acres-jane-smiley/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/a-thousand-acres-jane-smiley.jpeg" data-orig-size="251,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="a thousand acres jane smiley" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/a-thousand-acres-jane-smiley-188x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/a-thousand-acres-jane-smiley.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240519 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/a-thousand-acres-jane-smiley-188x300.jpeg" alt="a thousand acres jane smiley" width="188" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/a-thousand-acres-jane-smiley-188x300.jpeg 188w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/a-thousand-acres-jane-smiley-38x60.jpeg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/a-thousand-acres-jane-smiley-31x50.jpeg 31w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/a-thousand-acres-jane-smiley.jpeg 251w" sizes="(max-width: 188px) 100vw, 188px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781400033836" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>A Thousand Acres</em></a><br />
by Jane Smiley</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">Smiley&#8217;s beloved, Pulitzer Prize-winning novel transplants the intergenerational drama of Shakespeare&#8217;s King Lear onto an Iowan farm.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780767919371" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240520" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/the-life-and-times-of-the-thunderbolt-kid/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-life-and-times-of-the-thunderbolt-kid.jpeg" data-orig-size="257,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="the life and times of the thunderbolt kid" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-life-and-times-of-the-thunderbolt-kid-193x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-life-and-times-of-the-thunderbolt-kid.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240520 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-life-and-times-of-the-thunderbolt-kid-193x300.jpeg" alt="" width="193" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-life-and-times-of-the-thunderbolt-kid-193x300.jpeg 193w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-life-and-times-of-the-thunderbolt-kid-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-life-and-times-of-the-thunderbolt-kid-32x50.jpeg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-life-and-times-of-the-thunderbolt-kid.jpeg 257w" sizes="(max-width: 193px) 100vw, 193px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780767919371" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Life and Times of the Thunderbolt Kid</em></a><br />
by Bill Bryson</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">Bryson, best known for <em>A Walk in the Woods</em>, was born in Des Moines in 1951; this memoir is an often-hilarious and thoroughly nostalgic account of his childhood. [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Des+Moines,+IA/@41.5667265,-93.7713243,11z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x87ee99a4c1611ee7:0x710028512691e4b2!8m2!3d41.5868417!4d-93.6249522!16zL20vMDJqM3c?entry=ttu" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241535" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-tx/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-tx.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill tx" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-tx-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-tx.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241535" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-tx.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-tx.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-tx-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-tx-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-tx-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-tx-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.poetryfoundation.org/poets/d-a-powell" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">D.A. Powell</a></h2>
<p>Powell wrote the bulk of his first collection, <em>Tea</em>, while he was a grad student at Iowa; the landscape permeates its pages. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/zpwKttdqXuh8m2a87" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241217" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/iowa-5/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/iowa.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="iowa" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/iowa.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/iowa.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241217" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/iowa.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/iowa.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/iowa-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/iowa-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/iowa-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/iowa-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/iowa-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></h2>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong><a href="https://www.prairielights.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Prairie Lights</a>, Iowa City</h2>
<p>A beloved bookstore—and showcase for buzzy writers—in a designated UNESCO World City of Literature. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://www.prairielights.com/about-us" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/Iowa/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more on Literary Iowa</a></strong></h2>
