<h1>Kansas</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong><a href="https://www.ravenbookstore.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Raven Bookstore</a>, Lawrence</h2>
<p>In 2019, owner Danny Caine compiled a zine called “How to Resist Amazon and Why,” which has become a rallying cry for readers and independent bookstores alike. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/snAgTaEpGbAvJdf38" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780679745587" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="27021" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/gluttony-a-thanksgiving-reading-list/51b3c0ad8a8a6-image/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/51b3c0ad8a8a6.image_.jpg" data-orig-size="316,473" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="in cold blood" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/51b3c0ad8a8a6.image_-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/51b3c0ad8a8a6.image_.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-27021 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/51b3c0ad8a8a6.image_-200x300.jpg" alt="Truman Capote, In Cold Blood" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/51b3c0ad8a8a6.image_-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/51b3c0ad8a8a6.image_-100x150.jpg 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/51b3c0ad8a8a6.image_.jpg 316w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780679745587" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>In Cold Blood</em></a><br />
by Truman Capote</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">This &#8220;nonfiction novel,&#8221; first published as a four-part series in<em> The New Yorker</em>, recounts the 1959 murders of the Clutter family in Holcomb, a farming community in southwest Kansas. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/qFPGDvQcXfNUtvHZ6" target="_blank">MAP</a>] <em>See also</em>: <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781582435688" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Mrs. Bridge</em></a> by Evan S. Connell</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781501133107" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="99557" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/heartland-9781501133091_hr/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/heartland-9781501133091_hr.jpg" data-orig-size="1400,2146" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="heartland-9781501133091_hr" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/heartland-9781501133091_hr-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/heartland-9781501133091_hr-668x1024.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-99557 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/heartland-9781501133091_hr-196x300.jpg" alt="Sarah Smarsh, Heartland" width="196" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/heartland-9781501133091_hr-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/heartland-9781501133091_hr-768x1177.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/heartland-9781501133091_hr-668x1024.jpg 668w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/heartland-9781501133091_hr.jpg 1400w" sizes="(max-width: 196px) 100vw, 196px" /></a></p>
<h4></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781501133107" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Heartland</em></a><br />
by Sarah Smarsh</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">A memoir that doubles as a cultural examination of socioeconomic disparities in America, written by a fifth-generation Kansan. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/EroajDJXR8NwMBrMA" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241519" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-arizona/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill arizona" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241519" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.poetryfoundation.org/poets/william-e-stafford" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">William E. Stafford</a></h2>
<p>The prolific poet of the Great Plains won a National Book Award for <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781014235244" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Traveling through the Dark</em></a> in 1963. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/bCtGrV16xqaKevf2A" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241218" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/hughes-4/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/hughes.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="hughes" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/hughes.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/hughes.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241218" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/hughes.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/hughes.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/hughes-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/hughes-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/hughes-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/hughes-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/hughes-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong>732 Alabama Street, Lawrence</h2>
<p>Langston Hughes lived here as a child with his maternal grandmother. The house was demolished in the &#8217;60s, but a nearly identical one still sits next door. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/uMj6Ux6KdHoZDEbw5" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/kansas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more on Literary Kansas</a></strong></h2>
<p><span id="kentucky-cardinal"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241346" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/kentucky-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/kentucky-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,532" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="kentucky copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/kentucky-copy-300x133.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/kentucky-copy.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-241346" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/kentucky-copy.jpg" alt="" width="850" height="377" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/kentucky-copy.jpg 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/kentucky-copy-300x133.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/kentucky-copy-768x340.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/kentucky-copy-60x27.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/kentucky-copy-50x22.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px" /></span></p>
<h1>Kentucky</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong>Central Library, Lexington</h2>
<p>The world&#8217;s largest ceiling clock—complete with a five-story Foucault’s Pendulum—is housed within this library&#8217;s rotunda. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/FZ9M4YiziVDRD64MA" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781582431246" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240521" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/a-place-on-earth/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/a-place-on-earth.jpeg" data-orig-size="268,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="a place on earth" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/a-place-on-earth-201x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/a-place-on-earth.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240521 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/a-place-on-earth-201x300.jpeg" alt="" width="201" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/a-place-on-earth-201x300.jpeg 201w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/a-place-on-earth-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/a-place-on-earth-34x50.jpeg 34w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/a-place-on-earth.jpeg 268w" sizes="(max-width: 201px) 100vw, 201px" /></a></p>
<h4><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781582431246" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>A Place on Earth</em></a><br />
by Wendell Berry</h4>
<p>The 89-year-old writer-poet-activist lives and writes on a working farm in Henry County, from which he&#8217;s spun out many enduring, interwoven tales of the people in the fictional small town of Port William (inspired by his own hometown of Port Royal). [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps?sca_esv=2a19a3414e05e997&amp;output=search&amp;q=Port+Royal+kentucky&amp;source=lnms&amp;fbs=AEQNm0Aa4sjWe7Rqy32pFwRj0UkW1DRbm01j6DCVS0r1sTxn7h_rt6mVhwDmwtd3hPZjM8zcRGVTlPDZnJXk3Picr-AK624_I7oguu5Q8ldjEUSL4G_-MLpo6MCETap6IA7YuVw1FdAW0LTAF-gNrB9YytcGk1TLOgM4JSYTBumf_TpCimysxojSiYKvdzdomPGeDoU8LcMi&amp;entry=mc&amp;ved=1t:200715&amp;ictx=111" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>]</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780312423766" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240522" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/blood-horses-notes-of-a-sportswriters-son/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Blood-Horses-Notes-of-a-Sportswriters-Son.jpeg" data-orig-size="259,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Blood Horses- Notes of a Sportswriter’s Son" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Blood-Horses-Notes-of-a-Sportswriters-Son-194x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Blood-Horses-Notes-of-a-Sportswriters-Son.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240522 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Blood-Horses-Notes-of-a-Sportswriters-Son-194x300.jpeg" alt="" width="194" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Blood-Horses-Notes-of-a-Sportswriters-Son-194x300.jpeg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Blood-Horses-Notes-of-a-Sportswriters-Son-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Blood-Horses-Notes-of-a-Sportswriters-Son-32x50.jpeg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Blood-Horses-Notes-of-a-Sportswriters-Son.jpeg 259w" sizes="(max-width: 194px) 100vw, 194px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780312423766" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Blood Horses: Notes of a Sportswriter’s Son</em></a><br />
by John Jeremiah Sullivan</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">In Sullivan&#8217;s first book, he combines reflections on his relationship with his late father with an in-depth history of American horseracing. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/KavXxbHMQFRHCHHn9" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241517" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-copy-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241517" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.crystalewilkinson.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Crystal Wilkinson</a></h2>
<p>In <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780813151168" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Perfect Black</em></a>, Kentucky’s poet laureate explores her intersecting identities as a Black woman born in Appalachia. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/F4P9JzWxCtvxDEb29" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241348" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/bell_hooks_mural_ky/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bell_Hooks_Mural_KY.png" data-orig-size="2488,1802" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Bell_Hooks_Mural_KY" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bell_Hooks_Mural_KY-300x217.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bell_Hooks_Mural_KY-1240x898.png" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-241348" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bell_Hooks_Mural_KY-1240x898.png" alt="" width="1240" height="898" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bell_Hooks_Mural_KY-1240x898.png 1240w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bell_Hooks_Mural_KY-300x217.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bell_Hooks_Mural_KY-768x556.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bell_Hooks_Mural_KY-60x43.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bell_Hooks_Mural_KY-1536x1112.png 1536w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bell_Hooks_Mural_KY-2048x1483.png 2048w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bell_Hooks_Mural_KY-50x36.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1240px) 100vw, 1240px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong>bell hooks mural, Hopkinsville</h2>
<p>This hometown mural honors a woman deeply rooted in and shaped by the Western Kentucky landscape. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/R5JmATfe7TD8va8E7" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/Kentucky/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more on Literary Kentucky</a></strong></h2>
<p><span id="brown-pelican"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241342" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/louisiana-copy2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/louisiana-copy2.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,972" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="louisiana copy2" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/louisiana-copy2-300x243.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/louisiana-copy2.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-241342" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/louisiana-copy2.jpg" alt="" width="770" height="623" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/louisiana-copy2.jpg 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/louisiana-copy2-300x243.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/louisiana-copy2-768x622.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/louisiana-copy2-60x49.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/louisiana-copy2-50x41.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 770px) 100vw, 770px" /></span></p>
<h1>Louisiana</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong>City Park, New Orleans</h2>
<p>This park, dotted by 600-year-old live oaks and bordered by bayous, covers 1,300 acres. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/vXk3WxHsUaBB56VU7" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374214524" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240523" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/the-moviegoer-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-moviegoer-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="258,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="the moviegoer copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-moviegoer-copy-194x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-moviegoer-copy.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-240523 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-moviegoer-copy-194x300.jpg" alt="" width="194" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-moviegoer-copy-194x300.jpg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-moviegoer-copy-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-moviegoer-copy-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-moviegoer-copy.jpg 258w" sizes="(max-width: 194px) 100vw, 194px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374214524" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Moviegoer</em></a><br />
by Walker Percy</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">A young New Orleans stockbroker searches for meaning beyond artifice through a Mardi Gras quest; the result is an American masterpiece. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/fLPsKyVy5gZqfg8ZA" target="_blank">MAP</a>] <em>See also: <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781608196265" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Salvage the Bones</a> </em>by Jesmyn Ward</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780802149039" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="148997" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/looking-back-to-the-devastation-of-katrina-15-years-later/yellowhousepkmech-340x509/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/YellowHousePKMech-340x509-1.jpg" data-orig-size="340,509" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="YellowHousePKMech-340&#215;509" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/YellowHousePKMech-340x509-1-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/YellowHousePKMech-340x509-1.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-148997 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/YellowHousePKMech-340x509-1-200x300.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/YellowHousePKMech-340x509-1-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/YellowHousePKMech-340x509-1-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/YellowHousePKMech-340x509-1.jpg 340w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780802149039" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Yellow House</em></a><br />
by Sarah M. Broom</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">Broom melds memoir with sweeping historical narrative as she writes about her family history and childhood home as well as the vast racial inequities in the city of New Orleans. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/QTksmJPjB9oyFScj8" target="_blank">MAP</a>] <em>See also: <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780307718976" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Five Days at Memoria</a>l</em>, by Sheri Fink</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241523" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-ct/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill ct" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241523" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.jerichobrown.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jericho Brown</a></h2>
<p>Start with the Shreveport-born poet&#8217;s Pulitzer Prize-winning <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781556594861" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Tradition</em></a>, a lyrical collection about violence, identity, and legacy. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/85ceZkooiYws2SsA9" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241220" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/faulkner-7/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/faulkner.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="faulkner" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/faulkner.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/faulkner.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241220" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/faulkner.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/faulkner.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/faulkner-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/faulkner-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/faulkner-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/faulkner-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/faulkner-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong>Faulkner House Books</h2>
<p>At 624 Pirate&#8217;s Alley in the French Quarter, you&#8217;ll find this jewel-box bookseller tucked into the house where Faulkner lived and wrote his first novel, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593470961" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Soldier’s Pay</em></a>. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/X2A1KDHWfCc4W7Kq8" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/Louisiana/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more on Literary Louisiana</a></strong></h2>
<h2>(Or Spend a Literary Long Weekend in <a href="https://lithub.com/how-to-spend-a-literary-long-weekend-in-new-orleans/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">New Orleans</a>)</h2>
<p><span id="chicka-dee"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241315" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/maine-concept-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Maine-concept-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Maine concept copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Maine-concept-copy-300x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Maine-concept-copy-1024x1024.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-241315" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Maine-concept-copy-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="739" height="739" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Maine-concept-copy-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Maine-concept-copy-300x300.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Maine-concept-copy-150x150.jpg 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Maine-concept-copy-768x768.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Maine-concept-copy-60x60.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Maine-concept-copy-109x109.jpg 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Maine-concept-copy-100x100.jpg 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Maine-concept-copy-600x600.jpg 600w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Maine-concept-copy-50x50.jpg 50w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/u