<h1>Maine</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong><a href="https://www.novelmaine.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Novel Book Bar &amp; Café</a>, Portland</h2>
<p>Come for the cocktails and coffee roasted on-site, stay for the robust schedule of literary events. If you didn&#8217;t bring a book with you, no problem—you can find one on the shelves here (and bring it home with you when you&#8217;re ready to leave). [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps?sca_esv=2a19a3414e05e997&amp;output=search&amp;q=Novel+Book+Bar+%26+Caf%C3%A9,+Portland&amp;source=lnms&amp;fbs=AEQNm0Aa4sjWe7Rqy32pFwRj0UkW1DRbm01j6DCVS0r1sTxn7n1d7Mf3Iq8u18b0w9wQEnVrkfJ6Hb9xg9MtzDmfY0HJgL52upt53iqWyD_3wW1fEiuWV4gsghCTD2lct8XCm-xxsExO-qkN1GsVBoG7I-ZbvjmhxTXHRrul4Q6eMaRTjttZEO7Tp7onR80P0TJNKDZI7IPu&amp;entry=mc&amp;ved=1t:200715&amp;ictx=111" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780812971835" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="221102" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/everything-is-connected-a-reading-list-of-linked-stories/olive-kitteridge-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/olive-kitteridge.jpeg" data-orig-size="259,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="olive kitteridge" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/olive-kitteridge-194x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/olive-kitteridge.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-221102 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/olive-kitteridge-194x300.jpeg" alt="" width="194" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/olive-kitteridge-194x300.jpeg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/olive-kitteridge-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/olive-kitteridge-32x50.jpeg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/olive-kitteridge.jpeg 259w" sizes="(max-width: 194px) 100vw, 194px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780812971835" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Olive Kitteridge</em></a><br />
by Elizabeth Strout</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">A beloved novel in stories that explores the quiet, mysterious undertow of life in the coastal town of Crosby, Maine (fictional, but rumored to be based on Brunswick). [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Brunswick,+ME+04011/@43.8961584,-70.0548783,12z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x4cad8749da0b8999:0xaf7ab75ee4bdb4df!8m2!3d43.9140162!4d-69.966996!16zL20vMDFtNjB4?entry=ttu" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>] <em>See also: </em><em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781953534187" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Night of the Living Rez</a> </em>by Morgan Talty</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9798212942478" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240524" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/version-1-0-0-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/41ZOKNrQCVL.jpg" data-orig-size="328,500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Version 1.0.0&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Version 1.0.0&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Version 1.0.0" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Version 1.0.0&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/41ZOKNrQCVL-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/41ZOKNrQCVL.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-240524 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/41ZOKNrQCVL-197x300.jpg" alt="" width="197" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/41ZOKNrQCVL-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/41ZOKNrQCVL-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/41ZOKNrQCVL-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/41ZOKNrQCVL.jpg 328w" sizes="(max-width: 197px) 100vw, 197px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9798212942478" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Always, Rachel</em></a>: The Letters of Rachel Carson and Dorothy Freeman, 1952-1964<br />
ed. Martha Freeman</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">Impassioned correspondence between the great environmental writer and her close companion; the coast’s sublimity features often. [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Southport,+ME/@43.8157529,-69.697505,13z/data=!4m6!3m5!1s0x4cad9f3cf7f047ab:0x741d592652b1a79d!8m2!3d43.8409158!4d-69.6586568!16zL20vMHRxcl8?entry=ttu" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241520" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-arkansas/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill arkansas" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241520" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.poetryfoundation.org/poets/sarah-orne-jewett" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Sarah Orne Jewett</a></h2>
<p>Best known for prose awash in Maine’s landscape and tradition, her poetry, too, presents a vivid portrait of life in its seaport towns.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241222" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/maine-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/maine.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="maine" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/maine.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/maine.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241222" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/maine.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/maine.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/maine-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/maine-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/maine-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/maine-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/maine-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong>Stephen King House, Bangor</h2>
<p>The author’s Bangor Victorian sits behind a wrought-iron fence adorned with spiders and bats, and acts as an archive for writers, by appointment only. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/hqJzZpberUiZnw5eA" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/Maine/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more on Literary Maine</a></strong></h2>
<h2>(Or Spend a Literary Long Weekend in <a href="https://lithub.com/a-literary-long-weekend-in-portland-maine/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Portland</a>)</h2>
<p><span id="baltimore-oriole"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241309" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/md-concept-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MD-concept-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,667" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="MD concept copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MD-concept-copy-300x167.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MD-concept-copy.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-241309" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MD-concept-copy.jpg" alt="" width="789" height="438" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MD-concept-copy.jpg 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MD-concept-copy-300x167.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MD-concept-copy-768x427.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MD-concept-copy-60x33.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MD-concept-copy-50x28.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 789px) 100vw, 789px" /></span></p>
<h1>Maryland</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong><a href="https://www.library.jhu.edu/library-hours/george-peabody-library/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">George Peabody Library</a>, Baltimore</h2>
<p>An astonishing library with serpentine stairways that guide you to its centerpiece: the soaring stack room complete with tiered balconies. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/tgVK8Ra7hAnVjhCs9" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780449911594" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240677" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/dinner-at-the-homesick-restaurant-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Dinner-at-the-Homesick-Restaurant.jpeg" data-orig-size="648,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Dinner at the Homesick Restaurant" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Dinner-at-the-Homesick-Restaurant-194x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Dinner-at-the-Homesick-Restaurant.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240677 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Dinner-at-the-Homesick-Restaurant-194x300.jpeg" alt="" width="194" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Dinner-at-the-Homesick-Restaurant-194x300.jpeg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Dinner-at-the-Homesick-Restaurant-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Dinner-at-the-Homesick-Restaurant-32x50.jpeg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Dinner-at-the-Homesick-Restaurant.jpeg 648w" sizes="(max-width: 194px) 100vw, 194px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780449911594" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Dinner at the Homesick Restaurant</em></a><br />
by Anne Tyler</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">The domestic intimacies of the Tull family unfurl in Tyler’s ninth novel. In his review for The New Yorker, John Updike wrote that Tyler had &#8220;arrived at a new level of power.” [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/gNZ8MxKQZYgdfjsP7" target="_blank">MAP</a>] <em>See also</em>: <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780807083697" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Kindred</em></a> by Octavia Butler</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780812993547" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="23466" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/judging-the-national-book-award-shortlisters-by-their-covers/between-the-world-and-me-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Between-the-World-and-Me.jpg" data-orig-size="295,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1435153269&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Between the World and Me" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Between-the-World-and-Me-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Between-the-World-and-Me.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-23466 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Between-the-World-and-Me-197x300.jpg" alt="" width="197" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Between-the-World-and-Me-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Between-the-World-and-Me.jpg 295w" sizes="(max-width: 197px) 100vw, 197px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780812993547" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Between the World and Me</em></a><br />
by Ta-Nehisi Coates</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">In a letter to his son, Coates weaves stories of his life—beginning with his childhood at North Collington Avenue in West Baltimore—into an expansive American narrative. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/7EWvgTiNK5F9Fkwv6" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241525" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-del/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-del.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill del" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-del-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-del.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241525" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-del.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-del.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-del-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-del-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-del-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-del-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.poetryfoundation.org/poets/lucille-clifton" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Lucille Clifton</a></h2>
<p>Clifton’s work was first spotted by Langston Hughes, who published it in his 1970 anthology <em>The Poetry of the Negro</em>. In 1987, she became the first author to have two of her poetry books selected as finalists for the Pulitzer Prize.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241223" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/poe-6/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/poe.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="poe" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/poe.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/poe.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241223" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/poe.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/poe.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/poe-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/poe-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/poe-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/poe-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/poe-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong><a href="https://www.poeinbaltimore.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Edgar Allan Poe House</a>, Baltimore</h2>
<p>A life-size raven greets visitors at the home of this master of the macabre. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/RG1tZkHPYhRKoYmj7" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
