<h1>Massachusetts</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong><a href="https://www.gardnermuseuminc.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Gardner Museum</a>, Gardner</h2>
<p>The immersive art museum’s New Wing joins the glass-walled interior with the Monk’s, Jordan, and Lynch gardens—a special landscape for cracking open a book. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/7r5wNeFXDttnJ9DLA" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780147514011" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240678" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/little-women-10/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/little-women.jpeg" data-orig-size="286,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="little women" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/little-women-215x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/little-women.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240678 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/little-women-215x300.jpeg" alt="" width="215" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/little-women-215x300.jpeg 215w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/little-women-43x60.jpeg 43w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/little-women-36x50.jpeg 36w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/little-women.jpeg 286w" sizes="(max-width: 215px) 100vw, 215px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780147514011" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Little Women</em></a><br />
by Louisa May Alcott</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">The March women of Concord’s Orchard House have served as inspiration for generation upon generation of writers. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/HHnTvrfQeh3qBBjc8" target="_blank">MAP</a>] <em>See also</em>: <em>On Beauty </em>by Zadie Smith, <em>The Bell Jar </em>by Sylvia Plath</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="24710" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/behind-the-madness-of-the-salem-witch-hunt/schiff_thewitches/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Schiff_THEWITCHES.jpg" data-orig-size="500,758" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Schiff_THEWITCHES" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Schiff_THEWITCHES-198x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Schiff_THEWITCHES.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-24710 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Schiff_THEWITCHES-198x300.jpg" alt="Schiff_THEWITCHES" width="198" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Schiff_THEWITCHES-198x300.jpg 198w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Schiff_THEWITCHES.jpg 500w" sizes="(max-width: 198px) 100vw, 198px" /></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780316200592" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Witches: Suspicion, Betrayal, and Hysteria in 1692 Salem</em></a><br />
by Stacy Schiff</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">Schiff&#8217;s thrilling, meticulously researched account of the Salem witch trials will have you looking over your shoulder everywhere you go—and appreciating modern Salem all the more. [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps?sca_esv=2a9720fd994fa302&amp;output=search&amp;q=24+Liberty+St,+Salem,+MA+01970,+USA&amp;source=lnms&amp;fbs=AEQNm0Aa4sjWe7Rqy32pFwRj0UkW1DRbm01j6DCVS0r1sTxn7nH1uHtkwEIfd4YbKQci8nIBF_66ypoHzTkYRHzvgfdvualQL6mtZYNdb04qfSACp7yVz1EpxCIvhOoCtFSg40obYTeyHlxdAyXrNYFRoiUiEMDiFpeY2jDLeindHtzOSlneSBB2Dz05M5mXIVU-384JYUPO&amp;entry=mc&amp;ved=1t:200715&amp;ictx=111" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241522" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-colorado/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill colorado" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241522" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.poetryfoundation.org/poets/mary-oliver" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mary Oliver</a></h2>
<p>With wisdom, humor, and attention to every precious detail, Oliver&#8217;s <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780143124054" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>A Thousand Mornings</em></a> brings the reader along to the shore, ponds, and marshes surrounding the poet&#8217;s Provincetown home. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/p2HNeo6tf4pE9q3G8" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241294" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/the-mount-connecticut-v2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/The-mount-Connecticut-v2.jpg" data-orig-size="2348,1811" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The mount Connecticut v2" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/The-mount-Connecticut-v2-300x231.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/The-mount-Connecticut-v2-1240x956.jpg" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-241294" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/The-mount-Connecticut-v2-1240x956.jpg" alt="" width="1240" height="956" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/The-mount-Connecticut-v2-1240x956.jpg 1240w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/The-mount-Connecticut-v2-300x231.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/The-mount-Connecticut-v2-768x592.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/The-mount-Connecticut-v2-60x46.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/The-mount-Connecticut-v2-1536x1185.jpg 1536w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/The-mount-Connecticut-v2-2048x1580.jpg 2048w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/The-mount-Connecticut-v2-50x39.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1240px) 100vw, 1240px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong><a href="https://www.edithwharton.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Mount</a>, Lenox</h2>
<p>Edith Wharton’s sweeping estate in the Berkshires, which she designed herself, now functions as a house museum and cultural center. Don&#8217;t miss the pet cemetery. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/WmXAipn6uu5bLwB57" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/Massachusetts/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more on Literary Massachusetts</a></strong></h2>
<h2>(Or Spend a Literary Long Weekend in <a href="https://lithub.com/how-to-spend-a-literary-long-weekend-in-boston/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Boston</a>)</h2>
<p><span id="michigan-robin"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241407" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/michigan-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/michigan-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="michigan copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/michigan-copy-300x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/michigan-copy-1024x1024.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-241407" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/michigan-copy.jpg" alt="" width="796" height="796" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/michigan-copy.jpg 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/michigan-copy-300x300.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/michigan-copy-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/michigan-copy-150x150.jpg 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/michigan-copy-768x768.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/michigan-copy-60x60.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/michigan-copy-109x109.jpg 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/michigan-copy-100x100.jpg 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/michigan-copy-600x600.jpg 600w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/michigan-copy-50x50.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 796px) 100vw, 796px" /></span></p>
<h1>Michigan</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong>Tahquamenon Falls State Park, Upper Peninsula</h2>
<p>Row out to this park’s island encircled by five lower falls. Four miles upstream, the dramatic Upper Falls cascades nearly 50 feet down, across 200 feet. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/qRrLnv61tdhHrAJZ9" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780684169408" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240704" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/the-nick-adams-stories/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Nick-Adams-Stories.jpeg" data-orig-size="269,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The Nick Adams Stories" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Nick-Adams-Stories-202x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Nick-Adams-Stories.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240704 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Nick-Adams-Stories-202x300.jpeg" alt="" width="202" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Nick-Adams-Stories-202x300.jpeg 202w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Nick-Adams-Stories-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Nick-Adams-Stories-34x50.jpeg 34w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Nick-Adams-Stories.jpeg 269w" sizes="(max-width: 202px) 100vw, 202px" /></a></p>
<h4><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780684169408" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Nick Adams Stories</em></a><br />
by Ernest Hemingway</h4>
<p>These coming-of-age short stories were inspired by Hemingway’s summers at his family’s Northern Michigan cottage. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/Mko3MjCVYdcT2HXS9" target="_blank">MAP</a>] <em>See also</em>: The Jeffrey Eugenides oeuvre.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780062346636" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240705" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/black-detroit/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Black-Detroit.jpeg" data-orig-size="265,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Black Detroit" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Black-Detroit-199x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Black-Detroit.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240705 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Black-Detroit-199x300.jpeg" alt="" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Black-Detroit-199x300.jpeg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Black-Detroit-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Black-Detroit-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Black-Detroit.jpeg 265w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780062346636" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Black Detroit</em></a><br />
by Herb Boyd</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">Part memoir, part cultural history, Boyd&#8217;s illuminating take on Detroit explores the changemakers and freedom fighters who shaped (and continue to shape) the iconic city. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/KW5FMaUrgeqcYGgm6" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241521" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-california/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill california" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241521" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong>Lois Beardslee</h2>
<p>This Ojibwe poet’s collection <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780814347485" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Words Like Thunder</em></a> was the first book by an Indigenous author to win the Michigan Notable Book Award. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/x8G9PL2QffKbftb87" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241228" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/idlewild-3/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/idlewild.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="idlewild" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/idlewild.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/idlewild.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241228" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/idlewild.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/idlewild.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/idlewild-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/idlewild-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/idlewild-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/idlewild-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/idlewild-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong>Idlewild</h2>
<p>What began as a resort became a haunt for black intellectuals: Charles Waddell Chesnutt, W.E.B. DuBois, Langston Hughes, and Zora Neale Hurston rubbed shoulders here. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/Ce9WvePrzJyZXz558" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/Michigan/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more on Literary Michigan</a></strong></h2>
<p><span id="common-loon"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241403" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/minnesota-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/minnesota-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,1084" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="minnesota copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/minnesota-copy-300x271.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/minnesota-copy-1134x1024.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-241403" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/minnesota-copy.jpg" alt="" width="730" height="659" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/minnesota-copy.jpg 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/minnesota-copy-300x271.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/minnesota-copy-1134x1024.jpg 1134w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/minnesota-copy-768x694.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/minnesota-copy-60x54.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/minnesota-copy-50x45.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px" /></span></p>
<h1>Minnesota</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong><a href="https://www.mnhs.org/splitrock" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Split Rock Lighthouse</a>, Two Harbors</h2>
<p>The iconic lighthouse—which for a little extra literary flair, made an appearance in Baz Luhrman&#8217;s adaptation of The Great Gatsby—sits on a cliff 130 feet above Lake Superior, and is surrounded by a state park. Picturesque reading spots abound—if you can tear your eyes away from the view. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Split+Rock+Lighthouse/@47.1998393,-91.3729006,17z/data=!4m15!1m8!3m7!1s0x52af4b8cea85d0d7:0x65627e73283f851!2s3713+Split+Rock+Lighthouse+Rd,+Two+Harbors,+MN+55616!3b1!8m2!3d47.1998393!4d-91.3703257!16s%2Fg%2F11j3_slj72!3m5!1s0x52af4958ddf5c5bd:0x76eb8a39bcab80bc!8m2!3d47.1999918!4d-91.3670132!16zL20vMDV3bGJw?entry=ttu" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780062671134" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="184312" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-sentence/the-sentence/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/The-Sentence-.jpg" data-orig-size="429,648" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The Sentence" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/The-Sentence--199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/The-Sentence-.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-184312 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/The-Sentence--199x300.jpg" alt="The Sentence" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/The-Sentence--199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/The-Sentence--40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/The-Sentence--33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/The-Sentence-.jpg 429w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780062671134" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Sentence</em></a><br />
by Louise Erdrich</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">Erdrich&#8217;s (fictional) ghost story features the author’s real-life Minneapolis bookstore at its center. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/S4PkrS5VZKkwVYFJ9" target="_blank">MAP</a>] <em>See also</em>: <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780802127389" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>History of Wolves</em></a> by Emily Fridlund</p>
