<h1>Montana</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong><a href="https://www.missoulapubliclibrary.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Missoula Public Library</a></h2>
<p>With its state-of-the-art design and breathtaking scenic views, it’s no surprise that this spot was declared the “World’s Best Public Library” of 2022 by the World Library and Information Congress in Dublin, Ireland—the first library from North America to win the prestigious award. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Hearst+Free+Library/@46.1269843,-112.9556657,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x535b90cc6a22dc29:0x26475017ec7840a9!8m2!3d46.1269843!4d-112.953477!16s%2Fm%2F06_g43s?entry=ttu" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781571311467" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240709" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/perma-red-by-debra-magpie-earling/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Perma-Red-by-Debra-Magpie-Earling.jpeg" data-orig-size="324,499" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Perma Red by Debra Magpie Earling" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Perma-Red-by-Debra-Magpie-Earling-195x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Perma-Red-by-Debra-Magpie-Earling.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240709 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Perma-Red-by-Debra-Magpie-Earling-195x300.jpeg" alt="" width="195" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Perma-Red-by-Debra-Magpie-Earling-195x300.jpeg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Perma-Red-by-Debra-Magpie-Earling-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Perma-Red-by-Debra-Magpie-Earling-32x50.jpeg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Perma-Red-by-Debra-Magpie-Earling.jpeg 324w" sizes="(max-width: 195px) 100vw, 195px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781571311467" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Perma Red</em></a><br />
by Debra Magpie Earling</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">Debra Magpie Earling&#8217;s tale of a free-thinking woman on the 1940s Flathead Reservation holds stark present-day relevance. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Flathead+Reservation,+Polson,+MT/@47.4455394,-114.2584155,9z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x5367611da7966477:0xdbc8a87a709c0bc7!8m2!3d47.5002121!4d-114.3342905!16zL20vMDJqa2w3?entry=ttu" target="_blank">MAP</a>] <em>See also: <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780143106517" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Fools Crow</a> </em>by James Welch</p>
