<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong><a href="https://buttearchives.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Butte-Silver Bow County Archives</a></h2>
<p>The archives, you say? How exciting. But really: this is one of the best local history troves in America, documenting a wild city of mining millionaires and immigrant strivers. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Butte+Archives/@46.0153493,-112.5411353,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x535b09b3fd26a49d:0xcd3fa07ed1a27aa1!8m2!3d46.0153457!4d-112.5362697!16s%2Fg%2F1wrtcjcf?entry=ttu" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/Montana/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more on Literary Montana</a></h2>
<p><span id="nebraska-meadowlark"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241435" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/nebraska-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/nebraska-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,543" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="nebraska copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/nebraska-copy-300x136.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/nebraska-copy.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-241435" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/nebraska-copy.jpg" alt="" width="768" height="347" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/nebraska-copy.jpg 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/nebraska-copy-300x136.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/nebraska-copy-768x348.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/nebraska-copy-60x27.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/nebraska-copy-50x23.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px" /></span></p>
<h1>Nebraska</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong><a href="https://www.terracebookstore.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Terrace Books</a>, Columbus</h2>
<p>Grab a spot in a cozy armchair—or relax on the eponymous terrace—after finding a new favorite in this independent bookstore in historic downtown Columbus. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://www.google.com/maps?sca_esv=28d067ce084b4185&amp;output=search&amp;q=terrace+books+columbus&amp;source=lnms&amp;fbs=AEQNm0Aa4sjWe7Rqy32pFwRj0UkWM9PhT3xI6W-M3Wzu1YS_LhOvu-gm2PEGjtKNDePurfkOEZWP1bIxGM5xjx6Ywr_Rlp9bDjgpnzjYpcGUG6mGRk8A37pho__-B8EM4bviorhyDffp-TQzYgm-5oBZO5X64ItUrKKZSvejuDDrRY85bTXrIMCo3fxT-6ZhDnFjlNmH1uFI&amp;entry=mc&amp;ved=1t:200715&amp;ictx=111" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
