<h1>New Hampshire</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong>Diana&#8217;s Baths, North Conway</h2>
<p>After a gentle hike into White Mountain National Forest, you&#8217;ll find a series of small waterfalls and wading pools, with many spots for lounging. Try not to get your book wet. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Diana's+Baths/@44.0727467,-71.1726628,16z/data=!4m10!1m2!2m1!1sdiana's+baths!3m6!1s0x4cb3a1cb4461c2d5:0x40ff0bb34346effb!8m2!3d44.0747132!4d-71.1637945!15sCg1kaWFuYSdzIGJhdGhzWg8iDWRpYW5hJ3MgYmF0aHOSARJ0b3VyaXN0X2F0dHJhY3Rpb27gAQA!16s%2Fm%2F0jkz6_g?entry=ttu">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<h4><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593186879" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="136819" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/our-personalized-quarantine-book-recommendations-round-5/91yhblrdyl/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/91yhBlrDYL.jpg" data-orig-size="1464,2407" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="the world according to garp john irving" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/91yhBlrDYL-182x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/91yhBlrDYL-623x1024.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-136819 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/91yhBlrDYL-182x300.jpg" alt="the world according to garp john irving" width="182" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/91yhBlrDYL-182x300.jpg 182w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/91yhBlrDYL-623x1024.jpg 623w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/91yhBlrDYL-768x1263.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/91yhBlrDYL-36x60.jpg 36w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/91yhBlrDYL-934x1536.jpg 934w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/91yhBlrDYL-1246x2048.jpg 1246w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/91yhBlrDYL.jpg 1464w" sizes="(max-width: 182px) 100vw, 182px" /></a></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593186879" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The World According to Garp</em></a><br />
by John Irving</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">The author’s fifth novel and magnum opus tackles themes of feminism, sexuality, and literary ambition against the backdrop of a New Hampshire boarding school. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/PjkXa42uwN87YXWG6" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780802863263" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240714" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/jane-kenyon-a-literary-life/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Jane-Kenyon-A-Literary-Life.jpeg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Jane Kenyon- A Literary Life" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Jane-Kenyon-A-Literary-Life-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Jane-Kenyon-A-Literary-Life.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240714 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Jane-Kenyon-A-Literary-Life-200x300.jpeg" alt="" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Jane-Kenyon-A-Literary-Life-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Jane-Kenyon-A-Literary-Life-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Jane-Kenyon-A-Literary-Life-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Jane-Kenyon-A-Literary-Life.jpeg 667w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780802863263" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Jane Kenyon: A Literary Life</em></a><br />
by John H. Timmerman</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">This examination of the lyric poet&#8217;s life and work explores the construction of and inspiration behind her poetry as well as her lifelong struggle with manic depression. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/z75xWVcgfVJVLFyY9" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241536" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-nh/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-nh.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill nh" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-nh-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-nh.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241536" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-nh.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-nh.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-nh-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-nh-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-nh-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-nh-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.robertfrost.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Robert Frost</a></h2>
<p>Ever heard of him? The Dartmouth alumnus and Pulitzer Prize winner farmed and wrote in Derry, New Hampshire. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/oYPUQ3VPA2rK2awB7" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241236" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/joy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/joy.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="joy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/joy.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/joy.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241236" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/joy.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/joy.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/joy-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/joy-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/joy-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/joy-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/joy-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong>Joy Farm, Madison</h2>
<p>The treasured summer sanctum of E.E. Cummings is designated as a national historic place. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/uMwGb39hqRr1zegUA" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
