<h1>New Jersey</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong><a href="https://littlecitybooks.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Little City Books</a>, Hoboken</h2>
<p>Browse this much-loved corner indie shop, run by Donna Garban and Kate Jacobs. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/h4gWnE9G8VUxbjwL7" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780375701429" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="15612" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/americanpastoral-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/AmericanPastoral.jpg" data-orig-size="220,332" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="American Pastoral" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/AmericanPastoral-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/AmericanPastoral.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-15612 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/AmericanPastoral-199x300.jpg" alt="Philip Roth, American Pastoral" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/AmericanPastoral-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/AmericanPastoral-100x150.jpg 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/AmericanPastoral.jpg 220w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780375701429" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>American Pastoral</em></a><br />
by Philip Roth</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">Swede Levov’s rise-and-fall saga, set in 1960s Old Limerock, is the first novel in Roth&#8217;s American Trilogy, and won the Pulitzer Prize in 1998. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/qvNAeJHXQL7as2fz5" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374514426" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240717" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/the-pine-barrens/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Pine-Barrens.jpeg" data-orig-size="263,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The Pine Barrens" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Pine-Barrens-197x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Pine-Barrens.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240717 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Pine-Barrens-197x300.jpeg" alt="" width="197" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Pine-Barrens-197x300.jpeg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Pine-Barrens-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Pine-Barrens-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Pine-Barrens.jpeg 263w" sizes="(max-width: 197px) 100vw, 197px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374514426" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Pine Barrens</em></a><br />
by John McPhee</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">If everything you know about New Jersey&#8217;s Pine Barrens comes from that one episode of <em>The Sopranos</em>, this NJ nonfiction classic will open your eyes. [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/The+Pine+Barrens/@39.9501313,-74.5265853,15z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x89c16b768ffb0115:0x3695908fef2a47ef!8m2!3d39.9501159!4d-74.5162641!16zL20vMDJzOGhq?entry=ttu" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>]</p>
