<h1>New Mexico</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong>St. Francis Cathedral, Santa Fe</h2>
<p>Step into the silence of a Romanesque Revival church built on the site of an adobe chapel. Fun fact: Willa Cather&#8217;s <em>Death Comes for the Archbishop</em> includes a fictionalized story of its construction. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/7AnMXMRhHFJwSSPF9" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780446600255" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="193322" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/on-rudolfo-anayas-expansive-aching-view-of-childhood/bless-me-ultima/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bless-Me-Ultima.png" data-orig-size="566,858" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Bless Me, Ultima" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bless-Me-Ultima-198x300.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bless-Me-Ultima.png" class="size-medium wp-image-193322 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bless-Me-Ultima-198x300.png" alt="Bless Me, Ultima" width="198" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bless-Me-Ultima-198x300.png 198w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bless-Me-Ultima-40x60.png 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bless-Me-Ultima-33x50.png 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Bless-Me-Ultima.png 566w" sizes="(max-width: 198px) 100vw, 198px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780446600255" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Bless Me, Ultima</em></a><br />
by Rudolfo Anaya</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">Myth, love and destiny comingle in this coming-of-age classic, set in rural New Mexico in the 1940s. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/VvrvLqUDJATvavor9" target="_blank">MAP</a>] <em>See also: <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780062909954" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">House Made of Dawn</a> </em>by N. Scott Momaday</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781684580323" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240715" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/georgia-okeeffe-a-life-by-roxana-robinson/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Georgia-OKeeffe-A-Life-by-Roxana-Robinson.jpeg" data-orig-size="677,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Georgia O’Keeffe- A Life by Roxana Robinson" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Georgia-OKeeffe-A-Life-by-Roxana-Robinson-203x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Georgia-OKeeffe-A-Life-by-Roxana-Robinson.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240715 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Georgia-OKeeffe-A-Life-by-Roxana-Robinson-203x300.jpeg" alt="" width="203" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Georgia-OKeeffe-A-Life-by-Roxana-Robinson-203x300.jpeg 203w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Georgia-OKeeffe-A-Life-by-Roxana-Robinson-41x60.jpeg 41w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Georgia-OKeeffe-A-Life-by-Roxana-Robinson-34x50.jpeg 34w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Georgia-OKeeffe-A-Life-by-Roxana-Robinson.jpeg 677w" sizes="(max-width: 203px) 100vw, 203px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781684580323" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Georgia O’Keeffe: A Life</em></a><br />
by Roxana Robinson</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">This biography of Georgia O&#8217;Keeffe is also the story of New Mexico, the landscape she loved and painted. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/qro5EV5WrLKZ82zE6" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241522" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-colorado/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill colorado" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241522" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong>Joshua Concha</h2>
<p>Concha&#8217;s poem “Rust” was chosen as one of fifteen installed in outdoor venues in Taos, where he is Poet Laureate. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/GYqqNigZRAEWJbcLA" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark:</strong></h2>
<h4>D.H. Lawrence Ranch, Taos</h4>
<p>The novelist made his home here for a brief stint in the 1920s—enough time to write <em>St Mawr</em> and <em>The Plumed Serpent</em>. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/jqykyWac3DaAcvyq5" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/New-mexico/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more on Literary New Mexico</a></strong></h2>
