<h1>New York</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong>The Subway</h2>
<p>New York&#8217;s hottest reading spot is underground. Bonus points for the unmatched people (and title)-watching potential. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/aVgZ1y2jxVb3guPY9" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<h4><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780143137313" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240755" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/the-best-of-everything-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-best-of-everything.jpeg" data-orig-size="653,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="the best of everything" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-best-of-everything-196x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-best-of-everything.jpeg" class="wp-image-240755 size-medium alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-best-of-everything-196x300.jpeg" alt="" width="196" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-best-of-everything-196x300.jpeg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-best-of-everything-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-best-of-everything-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-best-of-everything.jpeg 653w" sizes="(max-width: 196px) 100vw, 196px" /></a></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780143137313" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Best of Everything</em></a><br />
by Rona Jaffe</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">Three women typists meet while working at a publishing house in this candid portrait of desire. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/YfFDsqbWxCgfv5Hj7" target="_blank">MAP</a>] See also: <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780375701870" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Go Tell It On the Mountain</em></a> by James Baldwin; <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780743273565" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Great Gatsby</em></a> by F. Scott Fitzgerald</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780679746317" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240756" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/up-in-the-old-hotel/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/up-in-the-old-hotel.jpeg" data-orig-size="259,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="up in the old hotel" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/up-in-the-old-hotel-194x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/up-in-the-old-hotel.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240756 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/up-in-the-old-hotel-194x300.jpeg" alt="" width="194" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/up-in-the-old-hotel-194x300.jpeg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/up-in-the-old-hotel-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/up-in-the-old-hotel-32x50.jpeg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/up-in-the-old-hotel.jpeg 259w" sizes="(max-width: 194px) 100vw, 194px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780679746317" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Up in the Old Hotel</em></a><br />
by Joseph Mitchell</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">This collection of essays chronicles encounters with the people of New York, all originally published in the New Yorker between 1943 and 1964. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/YfFDsqbWxCgfv5Hj7" target="_blank">MAP</a>]<em> See also</em>: <em>The Power Broker</em> by Robert A. Caro</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241520" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-arkansas/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill arkansas" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241520" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://alp.org/about/audre" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Audre Lorde</a></h2>
<p>1968’s <em>The First Cities</em> was Lorde’s first collection of poetry, but her very first poem was published while she was a student at Hunter High School. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/8Eu6N2KgQTD6bWYk6" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241239" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/nypl-3/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/nypl.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="nypl" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/nypl.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/nypl.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241239" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/nypl.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/nypl.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/nypl-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/nypl-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/nypl-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/nypl-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/nypl-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong>New York Public Library, Manhattan</h2>
<p>The lamplit Rose Reading Room is a Beaux Arts sanctuary. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/rMR25rMMdWBLSZed8" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
