<p><span id="nd-meadowlark"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241446" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/northdakota-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/northdakota-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,757" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="northdakota copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/northdakota-copy-300x189.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/northdakota-copy.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-241446" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/northdakota-copy.jpg" alt="" width="755" height="476" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/northdakota-copy.jpg 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/northdakota-copy-300x189.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/northdakota-copy-768x484.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/northdakota-copy-60x38.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/northdakota-copy-50x32.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 755px) 100vw, 755px" /></span></p>
<h1>North Dakota</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong>Badlands Overlook, Medora</h2>
<p>The rolling badlands panorama is perfect for spotting elk or bison wandering through the otherworldly buttes. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/mfA4x2eBa9QHru1f7" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781566895163" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="148012" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/here-are-the-greatest-novels-ever-written-about-every-sport/stephen-florida/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Stephen-Florida.jpg" data-orig-size="1600,2400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Stephen Florida Gabe Hudson" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Stephen-Florida-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Stephen-Florida-683x1024.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-148012 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Stephen-Florida-200x300.jpg" alt="Stephen Florida Gabe Hudson" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Stephen-Florida-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Stephen-Florida-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Stephen-Florida-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Stephen-Florida-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Stephen-Florida-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Stephen-Florida-1365x2048.jpg 1365w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Stephen-Florida.jpg 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781566895163" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Stephen Florida</em></a><br />
by Gabe Habash</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">In Habash&#8217;s debut novel, a college wrestler obsesses over a championship win; his loneliness is echoed in his surrounding landscape.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781324090861" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240760" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/boys-and-oil-growing-up-gay-in-a-fractured-land-by-taylor-brorby/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Boys-and-Oil-Growing-Up-Gay-in-a-Fractured-Land-by-Taylor-Brorby-.jpeg" data-orig-size="662,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1647609348&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Boys and Oil- Growing Up Gay in a Fractured Land by Taylor Brorby" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Boys-and-Oil-Growing-Up-Gay-in-a-Fractured-Land-by-Taylor-Brorby--199x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Boys-and-Oil-Growing-Up-Gay-in-a-Fractured-Land-by-Taylor-Brorby-.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240760 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Boys-and-Oil-Growing-Up-Gay-in-a-Fractured-Land-by-Taylor-Brorby--199x300.jpeg" alt="" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Boys-and-Oil-Growing-Up-Gay-in-a-Fractured-Land-by-Taylor-Brorby--199x300.jpeg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Boys-and-Oil-Growing-Up-Gay-in-a-Fractured-Land-by-Taylor-Brorby--40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Boys-and-Oil-Growing-Up-Gay-in-a-Fractured-Land-by-Taylor-Brorby--33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Boys-and-Oil-Growing-Up-Gay-in-a-Fractured-Land-by-Taylor-Brorby-.jpeg 662w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781324090861" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Boys and Oil: Growing Up Gay in a Fractured Land</a><br />
</em>by Taylor Brorby</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">Environmental activist Brorby&#8217;s lyrical account of growing up gay in the harsh and breathtaking landscape—and zero-stoplight town—of Center, North Dakota. [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Center,+ND+58530/@47.1152315,-101.3109931,15z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x52d83c09d4532dd1:0x1d9fd4a05cc6ba7c!8m2!3d47.1163849!4d-101.2995941!16zL20vMHlxNGw?entry=ttu" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241517" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-copy-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241517" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://poets.org/poet/denise-lajimodiere" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Denise Lajimodiere</a></h2>
<p>The Ojibwe poet and author of <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781946163103" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Stringing Rosaries</em></a> is the state’s latest laureate. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/t3eoGew84SyuTf9G6" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241241" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/lamour-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/lamour.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="lamour" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/lamour.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/lamour.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241241" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/lamour.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/lamour.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/lamour-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/lamour-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/lamour-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/lamour-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/lamour-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></h2>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong>Louis L’Amour Trail, Jamestown</h2>
<p>At 15, L&#8217;Amour joined a circus; then he wrote 100 novels of The West. Take a self-guided walking tour through the town where he spent his formative years. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/xDHuwJ4JrTUdcv916" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/north-dakota/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more on Literary North Dakota</a></strong></h2>
<p><span id="ohio-cardinal"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241448" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/ohio-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ohio-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="ohio copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ohio-copy-300x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ohio-copy-1024x1024.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-241448" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ohio-copy.jpg" alt="" width="705" height="705" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ohio-copy.jpg 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ohio-copy-300x300.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ohio-copy-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ohio-copy-150x150.jpg 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ohio-copy-768x768.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ohio-copy-60x60.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ohio-copy-109x109.jpg 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ohio-copy-100x100.jpg 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ohio-copy-600x600.jpg 600w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ohio-copy-50x50.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 705px) 100vw, 705px" /></span></p>
<h1>Ohio</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong>Kenyon College, Gambier</h2>
<p>Bring a book and spread out on the classic quad of the home to the esteemed <em>Kenyon Review</em>. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/ytAxZmWib62NvZ4n6" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781400033430" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="185374" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-36-best-old-books-we-read-in-2021/51edgrchnvl/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/51edgrCHnVL.jpg" data-orig-size="777,1198" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Toni Morrison, Sula" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/51edgrCHnVL-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/51edgrCHnVL-664x1024.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-185374 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/51edgrCHnVL-195x300.jpg" alt="Toni Morrison, Sula" width="195" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/51edgrCHnVL-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/51edgrCHnVL-664x1024.jpg 664w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/51edgrCHnVL-768x1184.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/51edgrCHnVL-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/51edgrCHnVL-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/51edgrCHnVL.jpg 777w" sizes="(max-width: 195px) 100vw, 195px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781400033430" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Sula</em></a><br />
by Toni Morrison</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">In Morrison&#8217;s masterful second novel, an omniscient narrator details the lives of the children Nel Wright and Sula Peace and their families in a tightly woven Ohio neighborhood—the Bottom, on the edge of Medallion. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/37uMyHfaqXEzC8Lo9" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781451692747" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240761" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/the-hard-way-on-purpose/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Hard-Way-on-Purpose.jpeg" data-orig-size="263,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The Hard Way on Purpose" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Hard-Way-on-Purpose-197x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Hard-Way-on-Purpose.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240761 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Hard-Way-on-Purpose-197x300.jpeg" alt="" width="197" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Hard-Way-on-Purpose-197x300.jpeg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Hard-Way-on-Purpose-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Hard-Way-on-Purpose-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Hard-Way-on-Purpose.jpeg 263w" sizes="(max-width: 197px) 100vw, 197px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781451692747" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Hard Way on Purpose</em></a><br />
by David Giffels</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">This collection of linked essays is an insider’s mining of an American Rust Belt story. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/SNnmSsGpvMNL5x5a8" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
