<h1>Oklahoma</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong><a href="https://www.metrolibrary.org/locations/northwest" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Patience S. Latting Northwest Library</a>, Oklahoma City</h2>
<p>This 35,000 square foot feat of glassed architecture resembles oil derricks and looks out on the prairie. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/ZktFKeUBxwjrYqfJA" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<h4><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780143039433" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="181391" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-25-most-iconic-book-covers-in-history/404px-the_grapes_of_wrath_1939_1st_ed_cover/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/404px-The_Grapes_of_Wrath_1939_1st_ed_cover.jpg" data-orig-size="450,667" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="404px-The_Grapes_of_Wrath_(1939_1st_ed_cover)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/404px-The_Grapes_of_Wrath_1939_1st_ed_cover-202x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/404px-The_Grapes_of_Wrath_1939_1st_ed_cover.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-181391 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/404px-The_Grapes_of_Wrath_1939_1st_ed_cover-202x300.jpg" alt="the grapes of wrath" width="202" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/404px-The_Grapes_of_Wrath_1939_1st_ed_cover-202x300.jpg 202w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/404px-The_Grapes_of_Wrath_1939_1st_ed_cover-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/404px-The_Grapes_of_Wrath_1939_1st_ed_cover-34x50.jpg 34w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/404px-The_Grapes_of_Wrath_1939_1st_ed_cover.jpg 450w" sizes="(max-width: 202px) 100vw, 202px" /></a></h4>
<h4><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780143039433" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Grapes of Wrath</em></a><br />
by John Steinbeck</h4>
<p>In this classic novel of the Great Depression, The Joads—a family of sharecroppers from Sallisaw—set out for California, in hopes of leaving Dust Bowl-induced drought, poverty and hardship behind. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/Dcv6s39p8fNPC7FPA" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780307742483" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="128315" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/literary-discos-summer-reading-2k19/killers-of-the-flower-moon-4/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Killers-of-the-Flower-Moon.jpg" data-orig-size="300,455" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Killers-of-the-Flower-Moon" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Killers-of-the-Flower-Moon-198x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Killers-of-the-Flower-Moon.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-128315 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Killers-of-the-Flower-Moon-198x300.jpg" alt="" width="198" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Killers-of-the-Flower-Moon-198x300.jpg 198w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Killers-of-the-Flower-Moon-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Killers-of-the-Flower-Moon.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 198px) 100vw, 198px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780307742483" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Killers of the Flower Moon</em></a><br />
by David Grann</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">In this hallmark true crime investigation, a journalist exposes the Osage Nation murders of the 1920s, a pivotal moment of prejudice that shaped the FBI. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/Dc9cz2sPePXFQ6Tz8" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241520" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-arkansas/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill arkansas" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241520" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.joyharjo.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Joy Harjo</a></h2>
<p>Harjo is a member of the Mvskoke Nation and the author of ten books of poetry, including <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780393358483" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>An American Sunrise</em></a>, winner of the 2020 Oklahoma Book Award. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/P2fyqy2doADozvGT6" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241243" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/guthrie/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/guthrie.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="guthrie" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/guthrie.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/guthrie.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241243" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/guthrie.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/guthrie.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/guthrie-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/guthrie-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/guthrie-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/guthrie-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/guthrie-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong><a href="https://woodyguthriecenter.org/" class="external" target="_blank">Woody Guthrie Center</a></h2>
<p>The folk hero was also a prolific writer of poetry and prose; his life’s work is celebrated here. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/c7xJmEVhdHNdNS6aA" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
