<h1>Oregon</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong><a href="https://sylviabeachhotel.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Sylvia Beach Hotel</a>, Newport</h2>
<p>This Oregon Coast hotel dates to 1918, each room with a literary theme. A little cheesy? Perhaps—but the purist wifi/TV/phone blackout is worth it. <a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://www.google.com/maps?output=search&amp;q=sylvia+beach+hotel&amp;entry=mc&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=2ahUKEwj-1I3cmqX_AhXNAjQIHZxtCt4Q0pQJegQIDBAB" target="_blank">[MAP]</a></p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<h4><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781590173244" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="134816" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/our-personalized-quarantine-book-recommendations-round-2/61vsemkmz0l/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/61vSEMKMz0L.jpg" data-orig-size="750,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="hard rain falling" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/61vSEMKMz0L-188x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/61vSEMKMz0L-640x1024.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-134816 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/61vSEMKMz0L-188x300.jpg" alt="hard rain falling" width="188" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/61vSEMKMz0L-188x300.jpg 188w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/61vSEMKMz0L-640x1024.jpg 640w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/61vSEMKMz0L-38x60.jpg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/61vSEMKMz0L.jpg 750w" sizes="(max-width: 188px) 100vw, 188px" /></a></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781590173244" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Hard Rain Falling</em></a><br />
by Don Carpenter</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">In which orphaned teenager Jack Levitt must live by his smarts on the streets of Portland. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/PxDyKzyUrB4brNjN7" target="_blank">MAP</a>] <em>See also: </em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781620400296" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Residue Years</em></a> by Mitchell Jackson</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781328507976" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="83271" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/no-time-to-spare_featured/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/No-Time-to-Spare_featured.png" data-orig-size="417,630" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="No Time to Spare_featured" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/No-Time-to-Spare_featured-199x300.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/No-Time-to-Spare_featured.png" class="size-medium wp-image-83271 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/No-Time-to-Spare_featured-199x300.png" alt="" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/No-Time-to-Spare_featured-199x300.png 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/No-Time-to-Spare_featured.png 417w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781328507976" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>No Time to Spare: Thinking About What Matters</em></a><br />
by Ursula K. Le Guin</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">A collection of personal musings on life and language from the venerated Oregonian that feels a little like sitting inside Le Guin&#8217;s Portland living room (which will soon be opened, along with the rest of her house, <a href="https://lithub.com/a-writing-residency-in-ursula-le-guins-home-is-the-closest-youll-get-to-earthseas-wizard-school/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">as part of a new writers residency</a>). [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Portland,+OR/@45.542595,-122.819552,11z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x54950b0b7da97427:0x1c36b9e6f6d18591!8m2!3d45.515232!4d-122.6783853!16s%2Fm%2F02frhbc?entry=ttu" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>]</p>
