<h1>South Dakota</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong><a href="https://www.fullcirclebookcoop.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Full Circle Book Co-op</a>, Sioux Falls</h2>
<p>A bookstore, art gallery, cafe, bar and gathering space all in one, nestled in the heart of Sioux Falls. [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps?sca_esv=247eb50602a83f19&amp;output=search&amp;q=Full+Circle+Book+Co-Op,+Sioux+Falls&amp;source=lnms&amp;fbs=AEQNm0Aa4sjWe7Rqy32pFwRj0UkW6GaBFdbzjCuzOWH_Sv7MGYvq6jLdN6MFCFptfCkV_BS7Vux8-VPwCy_PgKAN4Clw00fVxcQUPNWMHj2bfFP0QPMzVIQrlIbrVfWld2Z5pGVNNQVitJCHRRbR_ivnwxGrt4IUY8H6ikHMf2WGPGcGYipZnCPePPua2P7J1zIv8t3Pep_U&amp;entry=mc&amp;ved=1t:200715&amp;ictx=111" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780062968951" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240789" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/winter-counts/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/winter-counts.jpeg" data-orig-size="265,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="winter counts" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/winter-counts-199x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/winter-counts.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240789 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/winter-counts-199x300.jpeg" alt="" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/winter-counts-199x300.jpeg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/winter-counts-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/winter-counts-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/winter-counts.jpeg 265w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780062968951" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Winter Counts</em></a><br />
by David Heska Wanbli Weiden</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">A crime thriller set on the Rosebud Indian Reservation, where one man sets out to curtail the dangerous drugs pouring into his community. [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Rosebud+Indian+Reservation,+East+Todd,+SD/@43.1921845,-101.3725857,9z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x8778a93575dc206d:0xac07d3e01cd023e6!8m2!3d43.1875054!4d-100.6256931!16zL20vMDg3ZHdq?entry=ttu" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>]</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780143036210" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240790" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/the-journey-of-crazy-horse-a-lakota-history/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Journey-of-Crazy-Horse-A-Lakota-History.jpeg" data-orig-size="261,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The Journey of Crazy Horse- A Lakota History" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Journey-of-Crazy-Horse-A-Lakota-History-196x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Journey-of-Crazy-Horse-A-Lakota-History.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240790 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Journey-of-Crazy-Horse-A-Lakota-History-196x300.jpeg" alt="" width="196" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Journey-of-Crazy-Horse-A-Lakota-History-196x300.jpeg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Journey-of-Crazy-Horse-A-Lakota-History-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Journey-of-Crazy-Horse-A-Lakota-History-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/The-Journey-of-Crazy-Horse-A-Lakota-History.jpeg 261w" sizes="(max-width: 196px) 100vw, 196px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780143036210" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Journey of Crazy Horse: A Lakota History</em></a><br />
by Joseph M. Marshall III</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">The true story of the legendary Crazy Horse, drawn from oral histories and distilled by Lakota writer Marshall. [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Crazy+Horse+Memorial/@43.8366191,-103.6259787,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x8762cc001c5578df:0x7a29925e509a0c7!8m2!3d43.8366191!4d-103.6234038!16zL20vMDM3M3c0?entry=ttu" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241521" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-california/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill california" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241521" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.poetryfoundation.org/poets/lee-ann-roripaugh" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Lee Ann Roripaugh</a></h2>
<p>The former state poet laureate, author of <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781571314581" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Dandarians</em></a> and <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780809325696" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Year of the Snake</em></a>, among other books, teaches at the University of South Dakota and edits the South Dakota Review. [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps?sca_esv=247eb50602a83f19&amp;output=search&amp;q=University+of+South+Dakota,&amp;source=lnms&amp;fbs=AEQNm0Aa4sjWe7Rqy32pFwRj0UkW8Bt9bfRUVTzMU1CEv-WqPodRHT2B4xQ4lcpmeIYJ2nVL3ke1XMK7T2ta-4trQiibFbELpDp1G7izQlNWbTnH2n2TOx9STLNZEO2ocbfTlEIs9-yzOSS5a7RF1z4hNP_3IH7Ss8IzuzpUvnOxVSxZTv9pgE0b2brRCsCyxsPIKec44Wm-&amp;entry=mc&amp;ved=1t:200715&amp;ictx=111" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241250" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/ingalls/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ingalls.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="ingalls" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ingalls.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ingalls.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241250" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ingalls.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ingalls.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ingalls-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ingalls-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ingalls-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ingalls-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ingalls-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></h2>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong><a href="https://www.ingallshomestead.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Ingalls Homestead</a></h2>
<p>The little house on the prairie where Laura Ingalls Wilder lived and wrote offers covered wagon and pony cart rides, crafts, and other activities (laundry on a washboard, anyone?). [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps?sca_esv=247eb50602a83f19&amp;output=search&amp;q=Ingalls+Homestead,+De+Smet&amp;source=lnms&amp;fbs=AEQNm0Aa4sjWe7Rqy32pFwRj0UkW1DRbm01j6DCVS0r1sTxn7h_rt6mVhwDmwtd3hPZjM8zcRGVTlPDZnJXk3Picr-AK624_I7oguu5Q8ldjEUSL4G_-MLpo6MCETap6IA7YuVw1FdAW0LTAF-gNrB9YytcGk1TLOgM4JSYTBumf_TpCimysxojSiYKvdzdomPGeDoU8LcMi&amp;entry=mc&amp;ved=1t:200715&amp;ictx=111" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>]</p>
