<h1>Texas</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong>Barton Springs, Austin</h2>
<p>Bathe in this revered, 68-degree urban sanctuary, enjoyed by lap swimmers, sunbathers and plenty of dogs. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/VdmbH91GKs7iCMWk7" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781941920008" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240843" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/texas-the-great-theft/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/texas-the-great-theft.jpeg" data-orig-size="255,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="texas the great theft" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/texas-the-great-theft-191x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/texas-the-great-theft.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240843 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/texas-the-great-theft-191x300.jpeg" alt="" width="191" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/texas-the-great-theft-191x300.jpeg 191w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/texas-the-great-theft-38x60.jpeg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/texas-the-great-theft-32x50.jpeg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/texas-the-great-theft.jpeg 255w" sizes="(max-width: 191px) 100vw, 191px" /></a></p>
<h4><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781941920008" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Texas: The Great Theft</em></a><br />
by Carmen Boullosa, tr. Samantha Schnee</h4>
<p>Boullosa&#8217;s epic historical novel is a fresh and deeply absorbing reimagining of the history of Texas-Mexico borderlands. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/P1hkJeFynuEF1CMDA" target="_blank">MAP</a>] <em>See also</em>: <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781439195260" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Lonesome Dove</em></a> by Larry McMurtry, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780062409218" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">News of the World</a> </em>by Paulette Jiles</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780375727788" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240844" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/goodbye-to-a-river/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/goodbye-to-a-river.jpeg" data-orig-size="646,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="goodbye to a river" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/goodbye-to-a-river-194x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/goodbye-to-a-river.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240844 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/goodbye-to-a-river-194x300.jpeg" alt="" width="194" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/goodbye-to-a-river-194x300.jpeg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/goodbye-to-a-river-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/goodbye-to-a-river-32x50.jpeg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/goodbye-to-a-river.jpeg 646w" sizes="(max-width: 194px) 100vw, 194px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780375727788" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Goodbye to a River</em></a><br />
by John Graves</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">In 1957, Graves traveled down a stretch of the Brazos River by canoe just before a dam would destroy the river&#8217;s biome. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/EyaB6y7TN24Tutpn9" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241535" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-tx/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-tx.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill tx" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-tx-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-tx.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241535" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-tx.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-tx.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-tx-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-tx-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-tx-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-tx-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.carmentafolla.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Carmen Tafolla</a></h2>
<p>Tarfolla&#8217;s poetry of place centers on San Antonio, where she grew up in the West-Side barrios. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/TFzCzNzqv2tmV9qK8" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241253" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/lbj/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/lbj.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="lbj" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/lbj.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/lbj.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241253" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/lbj.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/lbj.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/lbj-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/lbj-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/lbj-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/lbj-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/lbj-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong><a href="https://www.lbjlibrary.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">LBJ Library</a>, Austin</h2>
<p>A recently renovated ode to the Stetson in the Oval, with an incredible collection focused on public policy. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/Z8gQn2Mp2ESFFbiS8" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
