<h1>Utah</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong>Bryce Canyon National Park, Bryce</h2>
<p>Wander through a maze of fantastic rock hoodoos, painted cliffs and wind-whipped alpine forests—the perfect spot for a little nature reading. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/Qbh55HDKUMGfWXTj7" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780385721813" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240846" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/when-the-emperor-was-divine-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/When-the-Emperor-Was-Divine-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="648,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="When the Emperor Was Divine copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/When-the-Emperor-Was-Divine-copy-194x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/When-the-Emperor-Was-Divine-copy.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-240846 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/When-the-Emperor-Was-Divine-copy-194x300.jpg" alt="" width="194" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/When-the-Emperor-Was-Divine-copy-194x300.jpg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/When-the-Emperor-Was-Divine-copy-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/When-the-Emperor-Was-Divine-copy-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/When-the-Emperor-Was-Divine-copy.jpg 648w" sizes="(max-width: 194px) 100vw, 194px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780385721813" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">When the Emperor Was Divine</a><br />
</em>by Julie Otsuka</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">Otsuka&#8217;s first novel, loosely based on family history, follows a Japanese American family living in Berkeley in the 40s, as they are suddenly &#8220;reclassified&#8221; and sent to an incarceration camp in Topaz, Utah. [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Topaz+Valley/@39.6832792,-113.6444664,10z/data=!4m10!1m2!2m1!1stopaz+utah!3m6!1s0x80b2e66ff8dd17a7:0x9786e5c2558c044c!8m2!3d39.6832791!4d-113.0841365!15sCgp0b3BheiB1dGFoWgwiCnRvcGF6IHV0YWiSAQZyYXZpbmWaASRDaGREU1VoTk1HOW5TMFZKUTBGblNVTkxhMXBFTjE5UlJSQULgAQA!16s%2Fg%2F1thvsz3q?entry=ttu" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>]</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780803293052" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240845" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/mormon-country/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mormon-country.jpeg" data-orig-size="273,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="mormon country" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mormon-country-205x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mormon-country.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240845 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mormon-country-205x300.jpeg" alt="" width="205" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mormon-country-205x300.jpeg 205w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mormon-country-41x60.jpeg 41w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mormon-country-34x50.jpeg 34w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mormon-country.jpeg 273w" sizes="(max-width: 205px) 100vw, 205px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780803293052" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Mormon Country</em></a><br />
by Wallace Stegner</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">Wallace Stegner&#8217;s 1942 chronicle of Mormon life in “lovely Deseret” captures the arid western landscape that the LDS community claimed in its search for a safe haven. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/hjb3TUdgaQVajuwA6" target="_blank">MAP</a>] <em>See also: <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780679740247" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Refuge: An Unnatural History of Family and Place</a></em>, by Terry Tempest Williams</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241521" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-california/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill california" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241521" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-california-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.paisleyrekdal.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Paisley Rekdal</a></h2>
<p>The decorated former Utah poet laureate is the author of seven collections of poetry, including <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781556596568" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>West: A Translation</em></a>, which commemorates the 150th anniversary of the completion of the transcontinental railroad, and which Rekdal has adapted into an <a href="https://westtrain.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">online multimedia project</a>. She directs the American West Center at the University of Utah. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/3t4auomoT4ZP4SBK7" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241483" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/arches_ut/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Arches_UT.png" data-orig-size="2284,1653" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Arches_UT" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Arches_UT-300x217.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Arches_UT-1240x897.png" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-241483" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Arches_UT-1240x897.png" alt="" width="1240" height="897" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Arches_UT-1240x897.png 1240w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Arches_UT-300x217.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Arches_UT-768x556.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Arches_UT-60x43.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Arches_UT-1536x1112.png 1536w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Arches_UT-2048x1482.png 2048w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Arches_UT-50x36.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1240px) 100vw, 1240px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong><a href="https://www.nps.gov/arch/index.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Arches National Park</a>, Grand County</h2>
<p>Edward Abbey spent two summers working here as a park ranger; the landscape informed his masterpiece, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780671695880" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Desert Solitaire</em></a>. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/q53qx4BobivpMogV7" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/Utah/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more on Literary Utah</a></strong></h2>
<p><span id="hermit-thrush"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241484" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/vermont-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vermont-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="vermont copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vermont-copy-300x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vermont-copy-1024x1024.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-241484" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vermont-copy-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="719" height="719" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vermont-copy-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vermont-copy-300x300.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vermont-copy-150x150.jpg 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vermont-copy-768x768.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vermont-copy-60x60.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vermont-copy-109x109.jpg 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vermont-copy-100x100.jpg 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vermont-copy-600x600.jpg 600w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vermont-copy-50x50.jpg 50w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vermont-copy.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 719px) 100vw, 719px" /></span></p>
<h1>Vermont</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong>Mad River Valley, Washington County</h2>
<p>Beloved for lazy river floats come summer, Mad River is paradise for rock climbers, readers, and sunbathers. Readers looking for a more pastoral backdrop will find it in the valley&#8217;s villages, where gabled barns and farms are stitched together by covered bridges. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/B6L4DET8t2vJkpZMA" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<h4><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781400031702" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="96110" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/40-of-the-best-villains-in-literature/22-secret-history-nocrop-w710-h2147483647-3/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/22-secret-history.nocrop.w710.h2147483647.jpg" data-orig-size="710,1095" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="22-secret-history.nocrop.w710.h2147483647" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/22-secret-history.nocrop.w710.h2147483647-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/22-secret-history.nocrop.w710.h2147483647-664x1024.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-96110 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/22-secret-history.nocrop.w710.h2147483647-195x300.jpg" alt="The Secret History, Donna Tartt" width="195" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/22-secret-history.nocrop.w710.h2147483647-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/22-secret-history.nocrop.w710.h2147483647-664x1024.jpg 664w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/22-secret-history.nocrop.w710.h2147483647.jpg 710w" sizes="(max-width: 195px) 100vw, 195px" /></a></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781400031702" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Secret History</em></a><br />
by Donna Tartt</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">Academic obsession leads a quintet of eccentrics into occult darkness at the fictional Hampden College in Donna Tartt&#8217;s cult classic. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/ySi5Btz8VtXV58sW7" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240847" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/version-1-0-0-3/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/41ERqPjv8ML.jpg" data-orig-size="332,500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Version 1.0.0&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Version 1.0.0&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Wandering Home: A Long Walk Across America&#8217;s Most Hopeful Landscape by Bill McKibben" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/41ERqPjv8ML-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/41ERqPjv8ML.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-240847 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/41ERqPjv8ML-199x300.jpg" alt="Wandering Home: A Long Walk Across America's Most Hopeful Landscape by Bill McKibben" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/41ERqPjv8ML-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/41ERqPjv8ML-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/41ERqPjv8ML-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/41ERqPjv8ML.jpg 332w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://billmckibben.com/wandering-home.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Wandering Home: A Long Walk Across America&#8217;s Most Hopeful Landscape</em></a><br />
by Bill McKibben</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">In his most personal book, Bill McKibben ruminates on wildness as he hikes from Vermont’s Mt. Abraham to the woods of the Adirondacks. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/qzodVPBkd885qsp17" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241522" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-colorado/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill colorado" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241522" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-colorado-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.poetryfoundation.org/poets/mary-ruefle" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mary Ruefle</a></h2>
<p>Mary Ruefle does it all. The poet (<a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781940696997" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Dunce</em></a>), lecturer (<a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781933517575" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Madness, Rack, and Honey</em></a>), and erasure artist (<a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781933517032" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>A Little White Shadow</em></a>) is also the beloved poet laureate of the Green Mountain State. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/EduHE72CL8VmWjhn7" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241256" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/bloaf/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/bloaf.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="bloaf" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/bloaf.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/bloaf.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241256" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/bloaf.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/bloaf.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/bloaf-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/bloaf-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/bloaf-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/bloaf-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/bloaf-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong><a href="https://www.middlebury.edu/school-english/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Bread Loaf School of English</a>, Ripton</h2>
<p>A mountain haven for writers since 1920, Bread Loaf is known for mustard-hued buildings and its program champion, Robert Frost, who taught there for 42 years. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/tAZ552DyjKS43MYAA" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/vermont/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more on Literary Vermont</a></strong></h2>
<p><span id="virginia-cardinal"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241485" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/virginia-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/virginia-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,564" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="virginia copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/virginia-copy-300x141.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/virginia-copy.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-241485" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/virginia-copy.jpg" alt="" width="744" height="350" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/virginia-copy.jpg 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/virginia-copy-300x141.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/virginia-copy-768x361.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/virginia-copy-60x28.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/virginia-copy-50x24.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 744px) 100vw, 744px" /></span></p>
<h1>Virginia</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong>Belle Isle, Richmond</h2>
<p>Sink into your book in this quiet, 54-acre island park in the midst of the James River. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/Ne7eDPfAepYcYvi77" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<h4><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780060557553" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="187083" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/81-writers-on-the-books-they-loved-in-2021/the-known-world-3/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/The-Known-World-.jpg" data-orig-size="265,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The Known World" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/The-Known-World--199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/The-Known-World-.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-187083 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/The-Known-World--199x300.jpg" alt="" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/The-Known-World--199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/The-Known-World--40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/The-Known-World--33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/The-Known-World-.jpg 265w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></a></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780060557553" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Known World</em></a><br />
by Edward P. Jones</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">Jones&#8217;s groundbreaking, Pulitzer Prize winning novel tells the story of Henry Townsend, a Black slave owner in antebellum Virginia, and the stories of those around him. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/eoeoUk7nUZFnXgPF9" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780393337761" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240852" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/the-hemingses-of-monticello/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-hemingses-of-monticello.jpeg" data-orig-size="266,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="the hemingses of monticello" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-hemingses-of-monticello-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-hemingses-of-monticello.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240852 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-hemingses-of-monticello-200x300.jpeg" alt="" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-hemingses-of-monticello-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-hemingses-of-monticello-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-hemingses-of-monticello-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/the-hemingses-of-monticello.jpeg 266w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780393337761" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Hemingses of Monticello</em></a><br />
by Annette Gordon-Reed</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">In Annette Gordon-Reed&#8217;s game-changing history of the Hemings family, we gain insight into the tangled web of family and exploitation that defined their lives, and the ways in which they fought for agency within an oppressive system. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/VFARSo8VqLuDjPwa7" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241525" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-del/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-del.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill del" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-del-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-del.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241525" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-del.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-del.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-del-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-del-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-del-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-del-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.poetryfoundation.org/poets/rita-dove" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Rita Dove</a></h2>
<p>The Pulitzer Prize winning poet, whose &#8220;<a href="https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2023/08/04/books/rita-dove-american-smooth-poem.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">American Smooth</a>&#8221; has quickly become a touchstone of contemporary verse, lives in Charlottesville and teaches at the University of Virginia. [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Charlottesville,+VA/@38.0400587,-78.5674049,12z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x89b3862dea50a48f:0x9086f096c38b74fc!8m2!3d38.0293059!4d-78.4766781!16zL20vMG1wM2w?entry=ttu" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>]</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241257" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/black-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/black.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="black" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/black.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/black.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241257" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/black.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/black.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/black-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/black-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/black-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/black-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/black-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong><a href="https://americanshakespearecenter.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Blackfriars Playhouse</a>, Staunton</h2>
<p>At the American Shakespeare Center&#8217;s Blackfriars, the world&#8217;s only re-creation of Shakespeare&#8217;s indoor theatre, you can enjoy performances of Shakespeare year-round [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/J4vnhSFdZvpzGE3m8" target="_blank">MAP</a>].</p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/virginia/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more on Literary Virginia</a></strong></h2>
<h2>(Or Spend a Literary Long Weekend in <a href="https://lithub.com/how-to-spend-a-literary-long-weekend-in-richmond-virginia/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Richmond</a>)</h2>
<p><span id="willow-goldfinch"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241486" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/washington-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/washington-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,746" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="washington copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/washington-copy-300x187.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/washington-copy.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-241486" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/washington-copy.jpg" alt="" width="735" height="457" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/washington-copy.jpg 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/washington-copy-300x187.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/washington-copy-768x477.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/washington-copy-60x37.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/washington-copy-50x31.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px" /></span></p>
<h1>Washington</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong>Main Street, Port Townsend</h2>
<p>At the very tip of the state, marked by a Jamestown S&#8217;klallam totem pole, tune into this Victorian port&#8217;s community with a coffee at Velocity, then walk a few blocks to get lost in two remarkable bookstores: indie gem Imprint and William James, a gobsmacking trove of used and rare. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/%E2%80%8BWilliam+James+Bookseller/@48.1143948,-122.7585745,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x548fedc696c81f97:0x4fb1057be54106f4!8m2!3d48.1143948!4d-122.7559996!16s%2Fg%2F1tf0253b?entry=ttu" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<h4><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780062868091" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="153787" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-cold-millions/coldmillions_cvr/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ColdMillions_cvr-scaled.jpg" data-orig-size="1686,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Jess Walter, The Cold Millions" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ColdMillions_cvr-198x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ColdMillions_cvr-675x1024.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-153787 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ColdMillions_cvr-198x300.jpg" alt="Jess Walter, The Cold Millions" width="198" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ColdMillions_cvr-198x300.jpg 198w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ColdMillions_cvr-675x1024.jpg 675w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ColdMillions_cvr-768x1166.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ColdMillions_cvr-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ColdMillions_cvr-1012x1536.jpg 1012w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ColdMillions_cvr-1349x2048.jpg 1349w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ColdMillions_cvr-scaled.jpg 1686w" sizes="(max-width: 198px) 100vw, 198px" /></a></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780062868091" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Cold Millions</em></a><br />
by Jess Walter</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">The acclaimed Spokane novelist brings the oft-forgotten radical history of the Northwest to life, taking on the riots over free speech and workers&#8217; rights that broke out in his city in the early 20th century. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Spokane,+WA/@47.6727552,-117.5940543,11z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x549e185c30bbe7e5:0xddfcc9d60b84d9b1!8m2!3d47.6587802!4d-117.4260465!16zL20vMDEwdjhr?entry=ttu" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781640095885" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="191852" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/indie-booksellers-recommend-the-best-of-independent-presses-this-february-and-march/screen-shot-2022-03-02-at-1-14-12-pm/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Screen-Shot-2022-03-02-at-1.14.12-PM.png" data-orig-size="372,604" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Red Paint: The Ancestral Autobiography of a Coast Salish Punk" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Screen-Shot-2022-03-02-at-1.14.12-PM-185x300.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Screen-Shot-2022-03-02-at-1.14.12-PM.png" class="size-medium wp-image-191852 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Screen-Shot-2022-03-02-at-1.14.12-PM-185x300.png" alt="Red Paint: The Ancestral Autobiography of a Coast Salish Punk" width="185" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Screen-Shot-2022-03-02-at-1.14.12-PM-185x300.png 185w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Screen-Shot-2022-03-02-at-1.14.12-PM-37x60.png 37w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Screen-Shot-2022-03-02-at-1.14.12-PM-31x50.png 31w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Screen-Shot-2022-03-02-at-1.14.12-PM.png 372w" sizes="(max-width: 185px) 100vw, 185px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781640095885" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Red Paint: An Ancestral Autobiography of a Coast Salish Punk</em></a><br />
by Sasha La Pointe</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">Profound and often wrenching, this power ballad of a book binds together two distinct Pacific Northwest threads: unbreakable Indigenous culture and underground rock-and-roll creativity. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Swinomish+Reservation,+La+Conner,+WA/@48.4168204,-122.5339504,12z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x54856524d2626bf3:0x2637bfbd05638c40!8m2!3d48.4164924!4d-122.5346109!16s%2Fg%2F121zcp6m?entry=ttu" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241523" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-ct/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill ct" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241523" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-ct-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.poetryfoundation.org/poets/richard-hugo" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Richard Hugo</a></h2>
<p>Bard of old docks and small-town bars, Hugo is also the patron saint of the Seattle literary center Richard Hugo House. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Hugo+House/@47.6161937,-122.3201071,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x54906acd0c141287:0x3863dc9041be7d2!8m2!3d47.6161937!4d-122.3179184!16s%2Fg%2F1yl45tz81?entry=ttu" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241259" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/carver-4/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/carver.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="carver" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/carver.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/carver.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241259" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/carver.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/carver.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/carver-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/carver-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/carver-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/carver-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/carver-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong>Raymond Carver&#8217;s grave, Port Angeles</h2>
<p>For a generation, Carver&#8217;s hard-bitten, sparse tales of working-class life defined the literary style of the modern Northwest. Born in an Oregon logging town, Carver spent his last years at the northern edge of the Olympic Peninsula, where a quietly elegant, low-key memorial is somehow perfect. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Ocean+View+Cemetery/@48.1306485,-123.5119665,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x548fadfd3297939b:0xf1248cab50753ad3!8m2!3d48.1306485!4d-123.5097778!16s%2Fg%2F1td17jzg?entry=ttu" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/washington/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more on Literary Washington</a></strong></h2>
<h2>(Or Spend a Literary Long Weekend in <a href="https://lithub.com/how-to-spend-a-literary-long-weekend-in-seattle/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Seattle</a>)</h2>
<p><span id="wv-cardinal"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241487" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/west-virginia-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/west-virginia-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="west virginia copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/west-virginia-copy-300x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/west-virginia-copy-1024x1024.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-241487" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/west-virginia-copy-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="717" height="717" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/west-virginia-copy-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/west-virginia-copy-300x300.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/west-virginia-copy-150x150.jpg 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/west-virginia-copy-768x768.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/west-virginia-copy-60x60.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/west-virginia-copy-109x109.jpg 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/west-virginia-copy-100x100.jpg 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/west-virginia-copy-600x600.jpg 600w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/west-virginia-copy-50x50.jpg 50w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/west-virginia-copy.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 717px) 100vw, 717px" /></span></p>
<h1>West Virginia</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong>New River Gorge, Fayetteville</h2>
<p>A whitewater river—one of the oldest on the continent—flows through deep canyons here. Scenic reading spots abound. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/ruiFKPqBuxcPmBQu7" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<h4><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780375705250" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240853" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/machine-dreams/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Machine-Dreams.jpeg" data-orig-size="644,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Machine Dreams" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Machine-Dreams-193x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Machine-Dreams.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240853 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Machine-Dreams-193x300.jpeg" alt="" width="193" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Machine-Dreams-193x300.jpeg 193w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Machine-Dreams-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Machine-Dreams-32x50.jpeg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Machine-Dreams.jpeg 644w" sizes="(max-width: 193px) 100vw, 193px" /></a></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780375705250" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Machine Dreams</em></a><br />
by Jayne Anne Phillips</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">Buckhannon native Phillips published this, her debut novel—the story of one family over some five decades in small town West Virginia—in 1984 to considerable acclaim. Her latest, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780451493330" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Night Watch</em></a>, is also set in West Virginia, and won the Pulitzer Prize for Fiction this year. [<a href="https://www.google.com/maps?sca_esv=c839f9702c677c11&amp;output=search&amp;q=Belington+west+virginia&amp;source=lnms&amp;fbs=AEQNm0Aa4sjWe7Rqy32pFwRj0UkW1DRbm01j6DCVS0r1sTxn7h_rt6mVhwDmwtd3hPZjM8zcRGVTlPDZnJXk3Picr-AK624_I7oguu5Q8ldjEUSL4G_-MLpo6MCETap6IA7YuVw1FdAW0LTAF-gNrB9YytcGk1TLOgM4JSYTBumf_TpCimysxojSiYKvdzdomPGeDoU8LcMi&amp;entry=mc&amp;ved=1t:200715&amp;ictx=111" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">MAP</a>]</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780743247542" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="136776" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/ten-memoirs-to-keep-you-company-in-isolation-a-reading-list/71vbpx0qsml-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/71VBpx0qsmL.jpg" data-orig-size="1400,2212" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="glass castle" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/71VBpx0qsmL-190x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/71VBpx0qsmL-648x1024.jpg" class="size-medium wp-image-136776 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/71VBpx0qsmL-190x300.jpg" alt="" width="190" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/71VBpx0qsmL-190x300.jpg 190w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/71VBpx0qsmL-648x1024.jpg 648w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/71VBpx0qsmL-768x1213.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/71VBpx0qsmL-38x60.jpg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/71VBpx0qsmL-972x1536.jpg 972w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/71VBpx0qsmL-1296x2048.jpg 1296w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/71VBpx0qsmL.jpg 1400w" sizes="(max-width: 190px) 100vw, 190px" /></a></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780743247542" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Glass Castle</em></a><br />
by Jeannette Walls</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">Memories of a West Virginia family both dysfunctional and free-spirited are the beating heart of Jeannette Walls&#8217;s 2005 memoir. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/L8phe2fgspE434aS6" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241520" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-arkansas/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill arkansas" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241520" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arkansas-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.poetryfoundation.org/poets/irene-mckinney" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Irene McKinney</a></h2>
<p>Raised on her family’s farm in Belington, McKinney writes poetry that explores the link between people, and place and mirrors the rural Appalachian landscape. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/SkrdQ7ZgZyMze54bA" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241260" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/johnhenry/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/johnhenry.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="johnhenry" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/johnhenry.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/johnhenry.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241260" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/johnhenry.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/johnhenry.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/johnhenry-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/johnhenry-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/johnhenry-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/johnhenry-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/johnhenry-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong>Talcott</h2>
<p>Legend has it that John Henry tried to show his strength as a railworker against a rock-drilling machine here; the story inspired Colson Whitehead’s novel <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780385498203" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>John Henry Days</em></a>. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/Q3Za6E5X2T6zjsnN6" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/west-virginia/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more on Literary West Virginia</a></h2>
