<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780826321930" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Wisconsin Death Trip</em></a><br />
by Michael Lesy</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">A mine is shut down in Black River Falls; this cult classic photobook recounts the grisly aftermath. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/eUExbpqm6TcbfT6v6" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241519" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-arizona/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill arizona" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241519" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-arizona-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.poetryfoundation.org/poets/lorine-niedecker" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Lorine Niedecker</a></h2>
<p>The introverted daughter of a carp fisherman, Niedecker spent most of her life in Fort Atkinson, where she wrote <em>New Goose</em> and <em>My Friend Tree</em>. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/GPa4C1uu6ceME4zX6" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241261" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/wis/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wis.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="wis" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wis.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wis.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241261" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wis.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wis.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wis-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wis-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wis-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wis-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wis-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong><a href="https://www.wisconsinhistory.org/Records/Article/CS15325" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Wisconsin Historical Society Library</a>, Madison</h2>
<p>Stately rows of green lamps glow in this library’s dreamy reading room. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/b6WgyQMQby6hzJ6N6" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/wisconsin/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more on Literary Wisconsin</a></strong></h2>
<p><span id="wyoming-meadowlark"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241489" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/wyoming-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wyoming-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,782" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="wyoming copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wyoming-copy-300x196.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wyoming-copy.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-241489" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wyoming-copy.jpg" alt="" width="712" height="464" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wyoming-copy.jpg 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wyoming-copy-300x196.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wyoming-copy-768x500.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wyoming-copy-60x39.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/wyoming-copy-50x33.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 712px) 100vw, 712px" /></span></p>
<h1>Wyoming</h1>
<h2><strong>Spot to Read: </strong><a href="https://www.whitebarklander.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Whitebark Bakery and Cafe</a>, Lander</h2>
<p>Lander, a small town with farm and ranch roots, has become a cultural and explorational hub. South of the Wind River Indian Reservation, on the cusp of the mountains, it now draws an adventurous crowd of climbers and hikers. Hang out here to absorb the far-flung creative ethos. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/rfpbmdK6MMyLoaMdA" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong>What to Read There:</strong></h2>
<h4><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780692443446" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240855" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/cowboys-and-east-indians/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Cowboys-and-East-Indians.jpeg" data-orig-size="267,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Cowboys and East Indians" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Cowboys-and-East-Indians-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Cowboys-and-East-Indians.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240855 alignleft" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Cowboys-and-East-Indians-200x300.jpeg" alt="" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Cowboys-and-East-Indians-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Cowboys-and-East-Indians-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Cowboys-and-East-Indians-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Cowboys-and-East-Indians.jpeg 267w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></a></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780692443446" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Cowboys and East Indians</em></a><br />
by Nina McConigley</h4>
<p style="text-align: left;">These short stories illustrate both Wyoming&#8217;s iconic landscape and its constantly shifting culture, weaving in a modern immigrant perspective on the West.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780805045437" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240856" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/grizzly-years/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/grizzly-years.jpeg" data-orig-size="267,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="grizzly years" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/grizzly-years-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/grizzly-years.jpeg" class="size-medium wp-image-240856 alignright" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/grizzly-years-200x300.jpeg" alt="" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/grizzly-years-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/grizzly-years-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/grizzly-years-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/grizzly-years.jpeg 267w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></a></p>
<h4 style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780805045437" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Grizzly Years</em></a><br />
by Doug Peacock</h4>
<p style="text-align: right;">In one of the most singular books about wilderness and wild things, a traumatized Vietnam vet communes with the grizzlies of Yellowstone. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/2n3teCiV19hEya2k9" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241517" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/quill-copy-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1.png" data-orig-size="1200,250" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="quill copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-300x63.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241517" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1.png" alt="" width="1200" height="250" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-300x63.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-768x160.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-60x13.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/quill-copy-1-50x10.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></h1>
<h2><strong>Poet of Note: </strong><a href="https://www.gretelehrlich.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Gretel Ehrlich</a></h2>
<p>Primarily known for her nonfiction, especially her 1985 essay collection about Wyoming, <em>The Solace of Open Spaces</em>, Ehrlich has also published poems of rural life and natural spaces in collections like <em>The Cold Heaven</em>.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="241262" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/a-literary-road-trip-across-america/vig/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vig.png" data-orig-size="300,300" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="vig" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vig.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vig.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241262" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vig.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vig.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vig-150x150.png 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vig-60x60.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vig-109x109.png 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vig-100x100.png 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/vig-50x50.png 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></p>
<h2><strong>Literary Landmark: </strong>The Virginian Hotel, Medicine Bow</h2>
<p>The mythology of the Western, as genre and archetype, dates back to Owen Wister&#8217;s 1902 novel <em>The Virginian</em>, set in this county and commemorated by this 1911-vintage hotel. [<a class="waffle-rich-text-link external" href="https://goo.gl/maps/h7EUPRPBv1eA1b8D9" target="_blank">MAP</a>]</p>
<h2><strong><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/Wyoming/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more on Literary Wyoming</a></strong></h2>
</p>										
																				
																		
